우선 안타깝게 돌아가신 사고 희생자분들의 명복을 빌며 유가족 분들에게도 위로의 말씀을 드립니다. 

영상을 업로드 하고 댓글들을 읽어 보았고 저의 
생각을 말씀드리는게 좋을것 같아서 이렇게 댓글로 말씀드려요.

10월29일 밤 이태원에서 정말 일어나서는 안되는 
사고가 일어났는데 아무런 일이 없다는듯 놀러
다니고 맛있게 먹는 영상을 업로드하는것은 사고 
희생자들에 대한 예의가 아닌것 같아서 다음날 
브이로그 채널에 광고 영상 업로드가 예정 되어있었지만 광고주님께 양해를 구하고 2주 뒤로 영상 일정을 미뤘으며 이틀 후 먹방 영상도 업로드 하지 않았습니다.

다만 제가 따로 커뮤니티에 글을 쓰지 않고 4일 
저녁에 업로드 한것은 비슷비슷한 애도 글을 커뮤니티에 올리는것이 무슨 의미가 있을까 싶기도 했고 애도 기간인 5일이 끝나고 기다렸다는듯이 영상을 올리는것도 제가 생각했을때 오히려 진정성이 없어 보일것 같아서 이렇게 일정대로 업로드를 하였습니다. 
오해가 있으셨다면 죄송합니다.

다시 한번 이태원 참사 희생자들의 명복을 빕니다.

Hi, guys! Today, I had the best deep-fried shrimp of my life!!!! I made giant deep-fried shrimp by using king tiger shrimp!!!!!!!! I also prepared tartar sauce, chili sauce, leaf mustard kimchi (Gat-Kimchi), and jalapenos!!! 🍤 These king tiger shrimps were full of plump, moist, sweet, and savory shrimp meat!!!!! Can you imagine how tasty it is...? It's much tastier than you imagine... Since I used bread crumbs, the thin batter on the outside was super crispy... (You can find out the recipe for the thin and crispy batter in the video 😉) The shrimp meat tasted like lobster...! While eating, I was deeply impressed by its amazing taste... 😭 It went well with savory tartar sauce & sweet and sour chili sauce! Especially, it was a good thing that I prepared leaf mustard kimchi! It was quite spicy 👍🏻 I've tried so many deep-fried shrimps in my life, but the one that I had today was the best... It was tastier than I expected, and I think I'll have this menu often!!!! Even now, I'm still thinking about its taste... If you like deep-fried shrimp, you should make it with king tiger shrimp!! Always be healthy and happy ❣

Halo semuanya! Hari ini, saya mendapatkan udang goreng terbaik dalam hidup saya!!!! Saya membuat udang goreng raksasa dengan menggunakan udang windu!!!!!!! Saya juga menyiapkan saus tartar, saus sambal, kimchi sawi daun (Gat-Kimchi), dan jalapeños!!! 🍤 Udang macan raja ini berisi daging udang yang montok, lembab, manis, dan gurih!!!!! Bisa dibayangkan betapa nikmatnya…? Daging udangnya terasa seperti lobster…! Sambil makan, saya sangat terkesan dengan rasanya yang luar biasa… 😭 Cocok dengan saus tartar gurih & saus cabai asam manis! Terutama, adalah hal yang baik bahwa saya menyiapkan kimchi mustard daun (Gat-Kimchi)! Itu cukup pedas! 👍🏻 Saya telah mencoba begitu banyak udang goreng dalam hidup saya, tetapi yang saya makan hari ini adalah yang terbaik… Rasanya lebih enak dari yang saya harapkan, dan saya rasa saya akan sering memiliki menu ini!!!! Hi, guys! Today I made Cheese Kimchi Fried Rice with spicy sour kimchi and mozzarella cheese! ❤ I also brought roasted Vienna sausages and Gyeranguk (egg soup) As you know, the key to delicious kimchi fried rice is tasty KIMCHI! All I did was just stir-fry green onions and add kimchi, perilla oil, and oyster sauce but it turned out so good!!! Both the texture and flavor were absolutely amazing! 👍🏻 I ate the fried rice with chewy cheese, and it was just sooo good!!! I also made cuts into Vienna sausages, and they were so good as well! When it comes to Vienna sausages, the thicker, the tastier! As I bite into it, it pops and the juice comes out! It also goes great with kimchi fried rice! Gyeranguk and kimchi fried rice also go great together! This combo is really simple and familiar but so delicious! No wonder Koreans love this combo! If you're looking for some food that can give you energy, how about trying the combo I ate today? Thank you for watching! I hope you are always healthy and happy! ❣

Hi, guys! Today I brought Mul Makguksu (Buckwheat noodles) (“Mul” means “water” in Korean!), Jeon, and Gatkimchi from Yeosu! As a Makguksu lover (I especially love Mul Makguksu!), I just had to eat Makguksu this time of year! I even used to travel all the way just to eat delicious Makguksu! I made Mul Makguksu using a meal kit, and it was really simple but turned out so well! It was so much better than I expected. The broth was refreshing, the noodles were really chewy, and I also love the combo of the savory flavor of perilla oil and the scent of buckwheat! Because of the sauce, It had a nice spicy finish, and I loved it! I got the gatkimchi from Yeosu! This was my first time eating Gat-kimchi with Makguksu, and it was sooo good!!! I highly recommend trying the two together, if you like Makguksu! 🥺 The jeon was so crispy on the outside and moist on the inside! It also went great with the soy sauce-marinated onions! All the combos I tried today were absolutely amazing! I think I’m going to miss all the foods I ate today all year round! 🤦🏻‍♀ It was pretty hot here, but I felt so recharged after finishing today’s meal! How about trying this combo today? Thank you so much for watching! I hope you are always happy and healthy!

Hi, guys! Today I brought Boneless Meat Gamjatang! I drank A LOT the previous day, so I was dying to eat something warm with broth! And then I stumbled across this boneless meat gGamjatang, so I got it delivered right away! It came with plenty of Ugeoji (dried cabbage) & meat! I ate them with a mustard dip, and it was so good! I added rice to the Gamjatang and I felt like all the fatigue was gone! 🥹 The Sujebi (hand-pulled dough) in the Gamjatang was also tasty and chewy! I also ate fried rice with broth, and it was just perfect! 💪🏻Eating fried rice is a must when eating Gamjatang! I don't think I've ever met anyone who doesn't like Gamjatang! I think the boneless meat Gamjatang I ate today would be perfect on days when you crave Gamjatang at home! It's super easy to eat! It's also great hangover food! Thank you for watching today! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

Herkese selam! Bugün Kemiksiz Gamjatang'ı (Domuz Omurga Çorbası) getirdim! Önceki gün ÇOK içtim, bu yüzden et suyuyla sıcak bir şeyler yemek için can atıyordum! Ve sonra bu kemiksiz Gamjatang'a (domuz omurga çorbası) rastladım, bu yüzden hemen teslim aldım! Bol miktarda kurutulmuş lahana yaprağı ve et ile geldi! Onları hardal sosuyla yedim ve çok iyiydi! Gamjatang'a (Domuz omurga çorbası) pirinç ekledim ve tüm yorgunluğun gitmiş gibi hissettim! Çorbadaki Sujebi (elle çekilmiş hamur) da lezzetli ve çiğnendi! Ayrıca et suyuyla kızarmış pilav yedim ve mükemmeldi! Gamjatang (Domuz omurga çorbası) yerken kızarmış pilav yemek bir zorunluluktur! Bundan hoşlanmayan biriyle tanıştığımı sanmıyorum! Bence bugün yediğim kemiksiz Gamjatang (Domuz omurga çorbası), evde canınız Gamjatang (Domuz omurga çorbası) çektiğiniz günlerde mükemmel olur! Yemek yemek çok kolay! Aynı zamanda harika bir akşamdan kalma yemeği! Bugün izlediğiniz için teşekkürler! Umarım her zaman sağlıklı ve mutlusundur!

Hi, guys! Today I ate Siraegi(dried radish greens) Jjimdak! ❤‍🔥 I ordered the spiciest flavored boneless Jjimdak! I added flat glass noodles, not regular, round ones. I also made this super soft Gyeranjjim (steamed eggs) for a side dish and brought white rice, Ssammu (pickled radish wraps), and Ddanmuji (pickled radish)! Of course, I made bibimbap with rice and sesame oil at the end! 😘 Since there was Siraegi in it, it was 100 times tastier than usual! Siraegi is a common ingredient for Ppyeojjim (braised back ribs). So it also kind of tasted like Ppyeojjim in a way! (It’s a great mix of Ppyeojjim and Jjimdak, I would say.) Anyway, it was nice and spicy! I really loved it! 🫢 There were lots of glass noodles in it, so if you like noodles like myself, I recommend eating them with well-seasoned Siraegi! It was a really satisfying meal of course, but it would’ve been much better if there had been more Siraegi 🥺 I’m definitely adding extra Siraegi next time! I especially loved the bibimbap I ate at the end of the meal. 🥹 All I did was add sesame oil, but it got even tastier!!! I also wrapped it with Gim, and it was so good that I basically inhaled it! Hi, guys! Today I brought Yakisoba Buldak Bokkeummyeon! It’s a limited edition that is only available in Japan. 🙌🏻 I also brought 3 kinds of takoyaki, katsuobushi, mayo, spicy pepper powder, and spicy peppers! When I took the first bite of the yakisoba, it tasted pretty sour! But then it started to taste like soy sauce and then the spiciness kicked in. It was less sweet than the original Buldak Bokkeummyeon, which was interesting! Since the noodles were thin, they were really well-seasoned with the sauce! Eating it alone was delicious, but it got like 100 times better with katsuobushi and mayonnaise! But it got less spicy, so I added some spicy pepper powder and spicy peppers. And then it got just perfect! Don’t forget to prepare sunny-side-up eggs when eating yakisoba, they are a match made in heaven! I especially loved eating takoyaki with yakisoba! It tasted heavenly! 👍🏻 The takoyaki was super moist on the inside and got a big piece of octopus! As far as I know, Buldak Yakisoba ramen isn’t available here in Korea. I hope we can also get it here! 😭 I think it’d be perfect when you crave yakisoba. If you get the chance, I highly recommend eating Yakisoba Buldak Bokkeummyeon with takoyaki and the ingredients I prepared today! Thank you for watching today! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

Hi, guys! Today I made 🔥Spicy Beef Rib Stew🔥 with beef ribs, spicy gochujang, and spicy pepper powder! Side dishes are white rice, baguette (my mom made it), and spicy chopped peppers! I’ve made cheese beef stew after 4 hours of cooking, and I thought it would be also delicious to make a stew with beef ribs! And it was a huge success! 😍 It was super soft and tender that it felt like I was eating cotton candy! It was really rich and juicy! And it had a nice and spicy finish. 😭🧡 It felt like my whole body was filled with happiness! It kind of tasted like Hayashi rice, but it also had a subtle flavor of tomatoes and went really well with both rice and bread! I later added some chopped peppers, and they added extra textures. They took the dish to another level! I really loved that I could enjoy various kinds of veggies and beef ribs at the same time! It was such a satisfying meal! 🫣 (I think even if you don’t like veggies, you would love this stew!) If you love meat, I highly recommend making this Spicy Beef Rib Stew! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

Hi, guys! Today is MALATANG DAY!!! (Finally!) 👀🔥 I’m sure you guys have been waiting for this day as well! Today I made this special malatang with Daechang (part of beef intestines) & my favorite ingredients and 6 kinds of fish balls! 😛 I also brought spicy pepper kimchi, white rice, and coriander! 🤤 I think malatang goes great basically with any ingredient! I wondered how good it would be to make malatang with Daechang, and it was just AMAZING!!! If you love malatang, I highly recommend making it with Daechang! The rich taste of Daechang and spicy broth go great together! I was so happy eating it! My favorite fish balls were the two kinds of fish balls my mom bought in Singapore! They are really big but super soft and chewy! You can just cut it with chopsticks! I especially loved the cheese fish ball! This was by far the best fish ball I’ve ever tried! Anyway, I was so happy eating malatang for the first time in a while thanks for your requests! (I’m definitely eating Mala Xiang Guo soon as well!) Today's MVP ingredients are definitely Daechang and cheese fish balls! I highly recommend making malatang with Daechang if you love malatang! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

Chào các bạn! Cuối cùng cũng đến ngày hôm nay!!!!! Đó là!!!!!! Ngày ăn lẩu Malatang 👀🔥 Các bạn cũng đợi lâu rồi đúng không ,,? Hari ini saya membuat malatang spesial ini dengan Daechang (bagian dari usus sapi) & bahan favorit saya dan 6 macam bakso ikan! 😛 Saya juga membawa kimchi lada pedas, nasi putih, dan ketumbar! 🤤 Menurutku malatang pada dasarnya cocok dengan bahan apa saja! Rasa yang kaya dari usus sapi dan kaldu pedas sangat cocok! Saya sangat senang memakannya! Bakso ikan favorit saya adalah dua jenis bakso ikan yang dibeli ibu saya di Singapura! Mereka sangat besar tapi sangat lembut dan kenyal! Anda bisa memotongnya dengan sumpit! Saya terutama menyukai bola ikan keju! Ini adalah bola ikan terbaik dalam hidupku! Bagaimanapun, saya sangat senang makan malatang untuk pertama kalinya dalam beberapa saat terima kasih atas permintaan Anda! (Saya juga akan segera makan Mala Xiang Guo!) Bahan MVP hari ini pastinya usus sapi dan bakso ikan keju! Saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat malatang dengan usus sapi jika Anda menyukai malatang! Saya harap Anda selalu sehat dan bahagia!

Hi, guys! Today, I made creamy Jin Jjamppong noodles that I made with milk and crispy sausage pastries! I also prepared cheese sauce, jalapenos, pickled radish, and chopped spicy chili pepper 🙌 You know that crispy fries always go well with creamy noodles? I was wondering if sausage pastries would go well with creamy noodles, but it was really perfect! Since I used milk, creamy Jjamppong gave a deeper and creamier flavor! If you love thick and creamy noodles, you would love this menu... 😭 As for the sausage pastries, there is spicy chili pepper sausage in the thin pastries dough! I love the texture of popping sausage and crispy pastry... Both the taste and the texture were awesome 👍🏻 How tasty it is!!!!!! Sausage pastries went more perfectly well with creamy Jjamppong than I expected! Especially, it was good to eat the pastry with noodles together! If you like cheesy, spicy, and creamy food, you should make this one with milk and enjoy it with sausage pastries! Thank you for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん。今日は牛乳で作った完全にコリクリーミーなクリームジンちゃんぽんにサクサクのソーセージペストリーをご用意しました！ チーズソース、ハラペーニョ、たくあん、辛い唐辛子も添えました🙌さくさくな揚げ物はこってりしたラーメン類にとても合う組み合わせなのはご存知ですよね？ ソーセージペストリーと一緒に食べても合うかなと思って持ってきたのですが、とても美味しかったです！ 🥹 クリームジンちゃんぽんは牛乳で沸かしてみたら、より深い味わいが感じられ、クリーミーさとコリっとした麺類がお好きでしたら、絶対に好きになるはず😭 ソーセージペストリーは外側は薄いペストリーが幾重にも重ねられていて、内側には辛い青陽唐辛子ソーセージが入っていました！ さくっと一口かじるとピリッと弾けるソーセージの味が絶品…。 味も食感もとても調和していました👍🏻感動の味!!!!ソーセージペストリーがクリームジンちゃんぽんソースとも期待以上によく合っていましたし、特にクリームジンちゃんぽん麺をのせて食べるのが一番おいしかったです🧡 とろおり、ピリ辛、こってりが好きな方は、家にある牛乳でクリームジンちゃんぽんを作ってソーセージペストリーを添えて召し上がってみてください！ 今日も視聴してくださって本当にありがとうございます！ 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made 8 servings of Pudding at home! 🫠💛 I added caramel syrup and whipped cream and then ate it with the Bocca pudding I bought in Hokkaido! I made the giant pudding with Carlnort pudding powder! It was super easy and so delicious! I loved it! (I mean, at least until I tried Bocca pudding...) Since I added whipped cream unlike the original recipe, it was slightly firm and had a deep creamy, custard flavor! I thought it would be really sweet, but it wasn't that sweet! So I could eat a lot. It was amazing that I could enjoy that much pudding just with a little bit of effort and money! Bocca pudding looks like turtle eggs, and it just melts in the mouth like cotton candy! It's got a deep milk flavor, I totally loved it! The caramel powder that came with the pudding was also really good! It tasted so harmonious! (It was such a shame that I only bought one bag 😭) If you like pudding, I highly recommend making pudding with pudding powder! It's super easy! Oh, and don't forget to try Bocca pudding if you get a chance! Thank you so much for watching! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日は家でプリンを8人分作りました!!!!大王プリンを作ってどんどんすくって食べることに成功...! ✔💛北海道で仕入れてきた亀の卵(探してみたら牧家プリンと呼ばれていました!)と一緒にキャラメルシロップとホイップクリームもかけて食べてみました! 大王プリンはCalnortのプリン粉で本当に簡単に作りましたが、味は期待以上でした！ 少なくとも亀の卵形の牧家プリンを食べるまでは…）生クリームの割合を高くして、少し固くて生クリームの風味が濃厚なカスタード味！ すごく甘いと思ったんですが、思ったより甘くなくてキャラメルシロップとホイップクリームをのせてどんどんすくって食べました😶 この味で、この値段で、この努力…? とてつもないコストパフォーマンス認定! 亀の卵のような形をした牧家プリンは綿菓子のように口の中でとろけるのですが、牛乳の味が本当に濃くて香ばしさを誇っていました。 同封されていたほろ苦いながらも甘いキャラメル粉もキメテ…! キャラメル粉の食感とプリンの食感が調和がとても完璧でした！ （なぜ一個だけ買ったんだと後悔しました）プリンが好きな方は家でプリン粉で手軽にプリンをいっぱい作って好きな時にたくさん食べてみたらいかがでしょうか！ 機会があればぜひ亀の卵プリンも召し上がってみてください! 今日も視聴してくださってありがとうございます！ いつも元気で幸せになってください❣

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membuat 8 porsi puding di rumah! 💛 Saya menambahkan sirup karamel dan krim kocok dan kemudian memakannya dengan puding bocca yang saya beli di Hokkaido! Saya membuat puding raksasa dengan bubuk puding carlnort! Itu sangat mudah dan sangat lezat! Aku menyukainya! (Maksud saya, setidaknya sampai saya mencoba puding bocca ...) karena saya menambahkan krim kocok tidak seperti resep aslinya, itu sedikit kuat dan memiliki rasa krim dan custard yang dalam! Saya pikir itu akan sangat manis, tapi itu tidak manis! Jadi saya bisa makan banyak. Sungguh menakjubkan bahwa saya bisa menikmati puding sebanyak itu hanya dengan sedikit usaha! Puding Bocca terlihat seperti telur penyu, dan itu hanya meleleh di mulut seperti permen kapas! Ini memiliki rasa susu yang dalam, saya sangat menyukainya! Bubuk karamel yang datang dengan puding juga sangat bagus! Rasanya sangat harmonis! (Sangat memalukan bahwa saya hanya membeli satu tas 😭) Jika Anda suka puding, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat puding dengan bubuk puding! Itu sangat mudah! Oh, dan jangan lupa untuk mencoba puding bocca jika Anda mendapat kesempatan! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! Saya harap Anda selalu sehat dan bahagia!

Chào các bạn! Hôm nay mình đã làm bánh flan khổng lồ 8 người ăn!!!!! Mình đã làm rất thành công... ! 🫠💛 Mình ăn cùng với bánh pudding trứng rùa mà mình đã mua ở Hokkaido (mình thấy có tên khác là Boka Pudding!), mình ăn caramel và kem tươi! Mình đã làm với bột bánh flan, thực sự rất dễ nhưng vị ngon thì vượt ngoài sự mong đợi của mình, vì vậy mình thực sự rất thích! (Ít nhất là cho đến khi bạn ăn bánh Pudding Boca trứng rùa...) Với tỷ lệ nhiều kem tươi, vị sữa trứng bông mềm mịn thực sự rất ngon! Mình nghĩ rằng sẽ rất ngọt, nhưng cũng không ngọt lắm, vì vậy mình ăn thêm với caramel và kem tươi 😶 Vị siêu ngon dễ làm mà giá lại rẻ nữa... ? Quá tuyệt vời các bạn à ... .! Boca pudding trông giống như quả trứng rùa, tan chảy trong miệng ngay như kẹo bông, vị sữa ngọt đậm đà làm mình không thể ngừng ăn được... Bột caramel ngọt bán kèm cũng rất tuyệt vời... ! Kết cấu của bột caramel, kết cấu của bánh pudding và sự hài hòa giữa chúng thật hoàn hảo! (Mình rất tiếc khi chỉ mua một cái à) Nếu các bạn thích bánh pudding, thì các bạn có thể dễ dàng làm tại nhà bằng bột bánh pudding và ăn bất cứ khi nào bạn muốn! Nếu có cơ hội, các bạn nhớ thử món pudding trứng rùa (boca pudding) nhé! Cảm ơn bạn đã xem video ngày hôm nay! Chúc các bạn luôn khỏe mạnh và hạnh phúc ❣

Hi, guys! Today I brought Spicy udon (Eomuk udon & pepper Eomuk udon) with Korean spicy pepper powder, Futomaki, and Egg Sushi! I later added some chopped chilies to the Udon. Side dishes are pickled garlic, pickled ginger, pickled radish, soy sauce, and spicy Kimchi! It's still pretty cold in Korea! After walking Mozzi, I craved warm udon, so I whipped it up! The noodles were super chewy and the broth was really refreshing and not too sweet! Since I added lots of pepper powder, it was pretty spicy! It was totally my style. I added some Yubu (fried tofu) pockets, and it was so delicious! The broth came out as I bit into it! 👍🏻 This was my first time eating udon with thin-cut Eomuk, and it was so good!!! The Eomuk played a huge role here. I later added some chopped spicy peppers, and they added a nice, spicy finish and crunchy textures. I loved it! The egg sushi was spongy and sweet, and the futomaki had various ingredients such as fried shrimp, salmon, tuna, etc. I think sushi or gimbap is the best side dish for udon! 🥰 I highly recommend adding Yubu pockets or thin-cut Eomuk when eating udon! Thank you so much for watching! I hope you are always happy and healthy! ❣️

Hi, guys! I LOVE braised beef feet, so today, I made Spicy Fire Jjajang Braised Beef Feet! I added flat Bunmoja (Chinese Hotpot Noodles), and I brought sunny-side-up eggs, spicy pepper kimchi, and rice balls! I sprinkled some chopped peppers and pepper powder as well. 🤤 I made it with Jjajang powder, beef feet that had been cooked for over 4 hours, Buldak sauce (Fire chicken sauce), green onions, onions, and pepper powder, and it was SO GOOD!!! I didn't know Jjajang sauce would go so great with braised beef feet! I personally liked it even better than rose-braised beef feet! The sauce wasn't greasy at all! It was rather sweet and spicy, so I think even people who don't like regular braised beef feet would love this! It was so well-seasoned and chewy and tender! It just melted in the mouth with the sauce. It's totally my kind of food! 😭🧡 Pepper kimchi also went well with it! Since I added flat Bunmoja, it also kind of tasted like Jjajangmyeon (Black bean noodles) or Jjajang Tteokbokki! Sunny-side-up eggs and rice balls were also a great combo! 🥺 Beef feet are not only tasty but also great for health! I highly recommend trying Spicy Jjajang Braised Beef Feet, especially if you're a fan of Braised Beef Feet! Thank you so much for watching! Hope you are always healthy and happy❣


こんにちは、皆さん！ 牛足蒸し大好きな私は、今日辛いプルチャジャン牛足蒸しを作ってしまいました!!!!!!!!中に平たい粉耗子も入れて、唐辛子キムチ、半熟フライ、辛い唐辛子、おにぎりまで用意しました! 唐辛子と唐辛子のトッピングもさっとかけました🤤 4時間以上じっくり煮込んでおいた牛足に四川ジャージャー麺の粉末+プルダックソース(玉ねぎ、ネギ、唐辛子粉)を入れて作りましたが、本当にX100おいしかったです、、こんなに牛足とよく合うとは思わなかったけど、個人的にロゼ牛足蒸しよりもっとおいしく食べました!!!! ジャージャーソースが期待以上の役割を果たしました！ 甘辛いから全然脂っこくないし、牛足が苦手な方も喜びそうな味！ タレが中まで染み込んでいるのに、もちしていてとても柔らかいです！ 口の中でジャージャーソースと一緒に溶けてしまうのですが、今日は本当にどストライク😭🧡さくさくと辛い味を詰め込んだ唐辛子キムチと一緒に食べたら幻想的な組み合わせ！ ジャージャーソースに平たい粉耗子まで入れたら、ジャージャー麺？ ジャージャートッポッキ？ を食べるようでした！ フライとおにぎりまで とても大満足な組み合わせでした🥺 体に良くて味も良い牛足！ 特に牛足蒸しが好きな方は、ぜひ召し上がってみてください🔥 今日も視聴していただきありがとうございます！ いつも元気で幸せになってください❣

Halo semuanya! Saya suka kaki sapi rebus, jadi hari ini, saya membuat Kaki Sapi Rebus Jjajang Api Pedas! Saya menambahkan Bunmoja pipih (Mie Hotpot Cina), dan saya membawa telur goreng, kimchi lada pedas, dan bola nasi! Saya menaburkan beberapa paprika cincang dan bubuk merica juga. 🤤 Saya membuatnya dengan bubuk jjajang, kaki sapi yang dimasak lebih dari 4 jam, saus buldak (saus ayam api), daun bawang, bawang merah, dan bubuk lada, dan itu sangat enak!!! Saya tidak tahu saus Jjajang akan sangat enak dengan kaki sapi yang direbus! Saya pribadi menyukainya bahkan lebih baik daripada kaki sapi yang direbus dengan saus mawar! Sausnya tidak berminyak sama sekali! Rasanya agak manis dan pedas, jadi saya pikir bahkan orang yang tidak suka kaki sapi rebus pun akan menyukainya! Itu sangat dibumbui dengan baik dan kenyal dan lembut! Itu hanya meleleh di mulut dengan saus. Ini benar-benar jenis makanan saya! Pepper kimchi juga cocok dengan itu! Karena saya menambahkan Bunmoja datar, rasanya juga seperti Jjajangmyeon atau Jjajang Tteokbokki! Telur goreng dan bola nasi juga merupakan kombo yang hebat! 🥺 Kaki sapi tidak hanya enak tapi juga bagus untuk kesehatan! Saya sangat merekomendasikan untuk mencoba Kaki Sapi Rebus Jjajang Pedas, terutama jika Anda penggemar Kaki Sapi Rebus! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! Semoga sehat dan bahagia selalu❣

Hi, guys 🙇🏻‍♀ Today, I prepared 3 cups of newly-released basil cream fire chicken udon, which is one of the fire chicken noodle series 💚🔥 and crispy rare salmon cutlet! ✨ As for the noodles, I added extra mozzarella cheese to make it creamier, and prepared tartar sauce! I was so excited to try it because I love basil! But, I was a bit embarrassed since it tasted like dried basil with strong flavors of fire chicken sauce rather than the fresh flavors of basil or cream 🤔 It was good, but it felt like something is missing! Anyway, cheese made it tastier! In my opinion, it would be better to use basil pesto sauce instead of dried basil... and more cream sauce 🥲 (I think we can add extra milk!) And it was spicier than I expected, so if you can't eat spicy foods, it would be hard for you to eat! But I loved those chewy udon noodles! The sauce made the noodles chewier and creamier!!!!! As for the salmon cutlet, I fried thick salmon! It felt like... eating raw salmon, fries, and salmon steak at the same time..! 🧡 It went well with tartar sauce, and I think it may go well with soy sauce and wasabi as well! It was a good idea to prepare salmon cutlet with basil cream fire chicken udon... 🤦🏻‍♀ Anyway, they went well with each other!!!!!!!! If you are going to try it, I recommend you add extra milk or cheese! And you should prepare crispy side dishes, too 🥰 Thank you for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん🙇🏻‍♀今日は韓国のプルダックポックンミョンシリーズで、今回新しく発売されたバジルクリームプルダックうどん3カップ💚🔥そしてサクサーモンレアカツを作りました！ ✨バジルクリームプルタクうどんはしっかりモッツァレラチーズたっぷり入れて、タルタルソースも用意してたっぷりつけて食べました! 私はバジルが大好きで、新しく出たバジルクリームプルダックうどんをすごく期待してました！ 初めて食べた瞬間、さわやかなバジルやクリーム味というより、乾バジル+プルダック味がパッと感じられて、予想していた味ではなく少し戸惑いました🤔 おいしいですが、個人的には少し残念な味！ チーズを入れて食べると確かにおいしいと思います！ 乾バジルではなく、むしろバジルペーストをソースに入れたらもっとおいしかったのではないかと思います。クリームの味ももっと濃かったらいいなとも思いました（牛乳を入れるならもっとおいしいかも？）辛さは思ったより辛くて、辛いのが苦手な方は召し上がるのが難しいかもしれません！ プリプリうどん麺は合格！ ソースと一緒に食べたらもちもち&ぷりしておいしかったです!!!! 鮭カツは厚めの鮭をカリカリに揚げたのですが、鮭の刺身と天ぷら、そして鮭ステーキ…？を一度に食べる味でした🧡 タルタルソースにつけて食べるとすごくおいしかったですが、わさびと一緒に醤油ソースにつけて食べてもおいしそうですよ！ バジルクリームプルダックうどんに鮭カツ食べなかったらどうするところだったんですか、、🤦🏻‍♀とにかく一緒に食べたからもっと美味しく食べられた組み合わせでした!!!! バジルクリームプルダックうどんをお召し上がりの方は、牛乳やチーズを入れて作ってみることをおすすめします！ サクサクのサイドも必ず用意して一緒に

Chào các bạn 🙇🏻‍♀Hôm nay là series mì vị gà cay Hàn Quốc, mình ăn 3 hộp mì udon gà cay sốt kem vị húng quế 💚🔥 Và mình ăn thêm cá hồi phủ bột chiên! ✨ Mì udon sốt kem mình có cho thêm nhiều phô mai mozzarella, chuẩn bị thêm sốt tartar để ăn cùng! Ngay khi nếm thử, mình cảm nhận được vị húng quế hơi ít+ vì cay nhiều hơn không phải hương vị như mình mong đợi nên cũng hơi bất ngờ 🤔 Vị ngon, nhưng có vẻ chưa hợp khẩu vị của mình lắm! Nếu cho thêm với phô mai, mình nghĩ sẽ rất ngon! Mình nghĩ nếu cho thêm Basil Pesto thì vị sẽ ngon hơn nhiều đấy, vị sốt kem béo hơn cũng sẽ rất tuyệt 🥲 (Cho thêm sữa cũng là ý tưởng hay?) Hari ini, saya menyiapkan udon ayam api krim kemangi yang baru dirilis, yang merupakan salah satu seri mie ayam api! dan irisan daging salmon langka yang renyah! ✨ Untuk mie, saya menambahkan keju mozzarella ekstra agar lebih creamy, dan menyiapkan saus tartar! Saya sangat bersemangat untuk mencobanya karena saya suka kemangi! Tapi, saya agak malu karena rasanya seperti kemangi kering dengan rasa saus ayam api yang kuat daripada rasa segar kemangi atau krim! 🤔 Bagus sih, tapi berasa ada yang kurang! Bagaimanapun, keju membuatnya lebih enak! Menurut saya, lebih baik menggunakan saus basil pesto daripada basil kering… dan lebih banyak saus krim 🥲 (Saya pikir kita bisa menambahkan susu ekstra!) Dan rasanya lebih pedas dari yang saya kira, jadi jika Anda tidak bisa makan makanan pedas , itu akan sulit bagimu! Tapi aku suka mie udon yang kenyal itu! Sausnya membuat mie lebih kenyal dan lembut!!!!! Sedangkan untuk potongan salmon, saya menggoreng salmon kental! Rasanya seperti… makan salmon mentah, kentang goreng, dan steak salmon sekaligus..! 🧡 Sangat cocok dengan saus tartar, dan menurut saya cocok juga dengan kecap asin dan wasabi! Merupakan ide yang bagus untuk menyiapkan potongan daging salmon dengan udon ayam api krim kemangi… 🤦🏻‍♀ Bagaimanapun, mereka cocok satu sama lain!!!!!!!! Jika Anda akan mencobanya, saya sarankan Anda menambahkan susu atau keju ekstra! Dan Anda juga harus menyiapkan lauk yang renyah! Terima kasih telah menonton video saya hari ini! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today’s dish is for egg lovers who especially like eating eggs with Tteokbokki sauce! I made super simple Spicy Stir-fried Eggs with Golden eggs, Soft-boiled eggs, and Quail eggs! I made it extra spicy with Cheongyang pepper powder and peppers! 🥰 Side dishes are white kimchi and Gim (Dried seaweed). I sometimes use my egg shaker to make golden eggs! Golden eggs made with an egg shaker have the texture of whites and taste like yolk! It’s very addicting, can you imagine the taste? 😭 I made today’s dish with these three different kinds of eggs, and both the taste and texture were AMAZING! 🙊💛 It was fun to pick which to eat next. The key ingredient for the sauce was Eomuk (fishcake)! I made it with ground Eomuk, and it tasted just like a Tteokbokki sauce from a popular Tteokbokki place! 👍🏻 The sweet and spicy sauce and eggs went great together! I personally liked it better with peppers! The combination of white rice, gim, white kimchi, and stir-fried eggs was just perfect! It’s also very well-balanced, nutrition-wise! If you’re an egg lover just like me, I highly recommend making today’s dish! I think I’m going to crave the taste every once in a while. Thank you so much for watching today! ❣️

Halo semuanya! Hidangan hari ini untuk pecinta telur yang sangat suka makan telur dengan saus Tteokbokki! Saya membuat Telur Tumis Pedas super sederhana dengan telur Emas, telur rebus, dan telur Puyuh! Saya membuatnya ekstra pedas dengan bubuk lada pedas dan paprika! Lauknya adalah kimchi putih dan rumput laut. Saya terkadang menggunakan pengocok telur untuk membuat telur emas! Telur emas yang dibuat dengan pengocok telur memiliki tekstur putih telur dan rasanya seperti kuning telur! Ini sangat membuat ketagihan, dapatkah Anda membayangkan rasanya? 😭 Saya membuat hidangan hari ini dengan tiga jenis telur yang berbeda, dan rasa serta teksturnya LUAR BIASA! 🙊💛 Sangat menyenangkan untuk memilih mana yang akan dimakan selanjutnya. Bahan utama sausnya adalah perkedel ikan! Saya membuatnya dengan perkedel ikan giling, dan rasanya seperti saus Tteokbokki dari tempat Tteokbokki yang populer! 👍🏻 Saus dan telur yang manis dan pedas sangat cocok! Saya pribadi lebih suka dengan paprika! Perpaduan nasi putih, rumput laut, kimchi putih, dan telur gorengnya pas banget! Ini juga sangat seimbang, dari segi nutrisi! Jika Anda pecinta telur seperti saya, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat hidangan hari ini! Saya pikir saya akan mendambakan rasanya dari waktu ke waktu. Terima kasih banyak telah menonton hari ini! ❣️

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日は韓国にありませんが、韓国人が好きな味のラーメン❤️私の大好きなラーメンでもあります！ さっそく日清チリトマトヌードルを持ってきました！ 🥺 チリトマトヌードルの3カップにソーセージとじゃがいも巻きエビも添えました! ほのかなチリ味の辛さとさわやかなトマト味が添えられて、一口食べると酔い覚ましのための辛いバージョンのトマトパスタが思い浮かぶ味！ 👏 日本のトマトのハイライスも本当においしかったですが、このラーメンもおいしいのを見ると、トマトが入るとだいたい私の好みに合うみたいです🙊実はこのラーメンを以前最初に食べた時は期待のない状態で食べたのですが、魅力的な味に驚いたのと同時に惚れました！ 具も大きめに入っていて(トマトキューブ、鶏、トウモロコシ、キャベツ、インゲン豆)具と粉末スープがすでにあるるので便利です! 🤭 普通に食べるより、やっぱりサイドと一緒に食べる方がずっとおいしいですよ！ 熱いラーメンに冷たいたくあんをのせて食べて、じゃがいも巻きエビとソーセージも一緒に食べると、カップラーメン3カップはあっという間に✨機会のある方はちょっと変わったラーメンのチリトマトヌードルを一度召し上がってみてください！ いつも元気で幸せになってください！

Chào các bạn! Hôm nay là món không có ở Hàn Quốc, nhưng rất được Hàn Quốc yêu thích ❤️ Cũng là món mì mà mình rất thích! Đó chính là mì Chili Tomato Nhật Bản! 🥺 Mình ăn 3 hộp với xúc xích tôm cuộn bột khoai tây chiên! Với vị cay nhẹ của ớt và vị chua ngọt của cà chua tươi, ăn miếng thôi khiến mình nghĩ ngay đến phiên bản cay mì pasta sốt cà chua! 👏 Món cơm thịt bò sốt cà chua của Nhật Bản cũng rất ngon, mì này cũng ngon, mình nghĩ món có cà chua trong đó khá hợp với khẩu vị của mình 🙊 Thực ra, lần đầu tiên mình ăn mì này trước đây, mình không kỳ vongjb lắm nhưng mình đã rất ngạc nhiên bởi hương vị hấp dẫn siêu ngon của mì! Ngoài ra còn có nhiều loại rau củ khô cỡ lớn (cà chua, thịt gà, ngô, bắp cải, đậu tây), và các nguyên liệu và súp bột đã được cho vào sẵn nên ăn rất tiện! 🤭 Ăn không cùng ngon nhưng ăn kèm với các món khác sẽ sẽ ngon hơn nhiều! Mình ăn mì nóng với củ cải ngâm chua mát lạnh, ăn cùng với khoai tây cuộn tôm chiên và xúc xích nên hết nhanh 3 ly mì. Nếu có cơ hội các bạn nên ăn thủ combo này nhé. Chúc các bạn luôn khỏe mạnh và hạnh phúc!

It went so great with Golbaengi and Eomuk, and it also added flavors and textures! It's a must when eating Golbaengi or Eomuk! Don't forget to add napa cabbage and radish! After enjoying the Golbaengi-tang and Korean-style cocktail, all the fatigue and stress were gone! 🥰 Golbaengi-tang is super easy to cook and delicious! I highly recommend it! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

مرحباً جميعاً! لقد صنعت اليوم حساء حلزون البحر الحار! (Golbaengi هو كوري للحلزونات البحرية!) ❤ أضفت أسياخ كعكة السمك ، والطبق الجانبي هو الثوم المعمر المحنك! 🤭 مشروب اليوم عبارة عن كوكتيل على الطريقة الكورية ، وماء منشط بنكهة الشاي الأسود ، وسوجو! 💚 كنت أتوق إلى حساء الحلزون البحري مؤخرًا. (أعتقد أن السبب جزئيًا هو أن الطقس في كوريا بارد جدًا!) لقد صنعته مع الكثير من Golbaengi والفجل وملفوف نابا والفلفل وعشب البحر و Eomuk (كعكة السمك). لقد قمت بطهيها بسهولة ، لكنها كانت جيدة جدًا !!! 🤤 كان الجمع بين المرق الحار وحلزون البحر الحلو والمطاطي مذهلاً! كان المرق مدمنًا لدرجة أنني انتهيت من شربه دون توقف! كانت كعكة السمك أيضًا طرية للغاية ولينة! لقد سارت الأمور بشكل رائع مع حلزون البحر ، لكنني أعتقد أن سارق المشهد اليوم هو ثوم المعمر المخضرم! لقد سار بشكل رائع مع حلزون البحر وكعك السمك ، كما أضاف النكهات والقوام! إنه أمر لا بد منه عند تناول حلزون البحر أو كعك السمك! لا تنس إضافة ملفوف نابا والفجل! بعد الاستمتاع بحساء الحلزون البحري الكوري (Golbaengi-tang) والكوكتيل على الطريقة الكورية ، ذهب كل التعب والإجهاد! حساء حلزون البحر الكوري (جولبانجي تانغ) سهل الطبخ ولذيذ! انا اوصي بشده به! شكرا جزيلا على المشاهدة اليوم! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Spicy Rice Cake Soup with Dumplings (Tteok-mandu-guk)! I made it with thin-skinned kimchi mandu and meat mandu. I think it took me only 5 minutes or so! Side dishes were 3 kinds of Kimchi: sour Kimchi, radish Kimchi (Seokbakji), and white Kimchi! It was spicy but got deep flavors because I used beef broth! I think it would be great hangover food! Mandu and cold kimchi go great together!👍🏻 I'm sure this is soul food for many Koreans. ⭐️ The combo of chewy Tteok (rice cakes), soft egg, and Gim (seaweed) was just AMAZING! It felt like all the stress that had been harassing me was just gone! 😳🧡 When you don't feel like cooking or you need hangover food, how about eating spicy rice cake soup with dumplings (Tteok-mandu-guk)? If you like tteok or mandu, I highly recommend trying Tteok-mandu-guk! Thank you so much for watching today! I hope you are always happy and healthy! ❣️

Hi, guys! Today I brought the incredible combo, Spicy Braised Rose Beef Feet & Spicy Pepper Kimchi! 🥺🧡 Side dish is rice balls!👍🏻 The rose Koreans love typically calls for Gochujang (chili paste) and pepper powder! So, I made the sauce with spicy pepper powder, spicy sticky rice Gochujang, starch syrup, salt, and milk! It took a whole day to remove the blood in the beef feet. And then I brought them to a boil for over 4 hours! It did take me a long time, but it's actually pretty easy! Once you bite into it, you'll feel rewarded! It's super chewy and goes perfectly with rose sauce! It's creamy but spicy, so it wasn't overly greasy or anything. It was so good!!! I added some chopped spicy peppers later, so it was also very crunchy. Loved the texture! I also ate pepper kimchi with it, and it was just unbelievable! If you love braised beef feet, I highly recommend eating braised rose beef feet with pepper kimchi! 😭🧡 Thank you so much for watching today! I hope you are always healthy and happy!

Hi, guys! Today I made Crab Curry (Pu Pad Pong Curry) with lots of crab meat! Pu Pad Pong Curry is one of the most famous Thai foods! You might think it's hard to make, but it's not! It's actually really simple and easy! I made it with crab sticks and crabs, but crabs are optional! I used Pu Pad Pong Curry powder, but you can also make it with regular curry powder, fish sauce, salt, vinegar, and milk! It was surprisingly delicious!!! The crab meat just melted in the mouth, and it went so great with the fried crab! I was craving crab curry so bad, so I was really happy eating it! The crab I added to the curry was well-seasoned and moist, and the fried crab was super crispy! If you love crab curry (Pu Pad Pong Curry), you MUST make it!!! It's not the traditional way, but it's very delicious! Thank you so much for watching today! I hope you are always healthy and happy! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membuat Kari Kepiting (Kari Pu Pad Pong) dengan daging kepiting yang banyak! Kari Pu Pad Pong adalah salah satu makanan Thailand paling terkenal! Anda mungkin berpikir itu sulit untuk dibuat, tetapi tidak! Ini sebenarnya sangat sederhana dan mudah! Saya membuatnya dengan tongkat kepiting dan kepiting asli, tetapi kepiting asli adalah opsional! Saya menggunakan bubuk Kari Pu Pad Pong, tapi Anda juga bisa membuatnya dengan bubuk kari biasa, kecap ikan, garam, cuka, dan susu! Ternyata sangat lezat!!! Daging kepitingnya baru saja meleleh di mulut, dan sangat cocok dengan kepiting gorengnya! Saya sangat menginginkan kari kepiting, jadi saya sangat senang memakannya! Kepiting yang saya tambahkan ke kari dibumbui dengan baik dan lembab, dan kepiting gorengnya sangat renyah! Jika Anda menyukai kari kepiting (Pu Pad Pong Curry), Anda HARUS membuatnya!!! Hi, guys 🙇🏻‍♀ Today, spicy food helped boost my happiness 🔥 I made spicy braised beef feet, which was really chewy 😋 I also prepared furikake rice balls, steamed eggs, and white kimchi! After eating some, I added spicy chili pepper as well 🌶 Beef feet were kept in the water to draw out blood, and it took almost 4 hours to make it.. But, it was worth the time ❤‍🔥 It was so soft that the fillets just fell off the bones, and the fillets just melted like snow in my mouth! If you like pork feet dishes, you should also try this tasty beef foot dish 🙊 Beef feet are savory in themselves, but they may be a bit greasy so spicy sauce and crunchy chili pepper make them much tastier! 🤭 Beef feet are rich in collagen, so they are really good for your health!!!!!! That means that there is no reason why you shouldn't try that! I was able to enjoy the meal more due to the rice balls which had the deep flavors of bonito, soft steamed eggs, and cold white kimchi! Today, I became happy thanks to those spicy foods 🤤 If you haven't tried braised beef feet, I hope you can have a chance to make and try them soon! Thank you for watching my video today! Always be healthy and happy ❣

Hi, guys! Merry Christmas! Today I made Spicy Golbaengi Jjim (braised sea snails) at home! ❤️💚It's a perfect food for Christmas 🎄 and also my Christmas ornament for this year! (Huh?) I brought two kinds of Golbaengi and made Golbaengi Jjim & Golbaengi Tang!👏 😍 I think the symbolic colors for Christmas are red and green, so I topped the Golbaengi with Cheongyang peppers! Since each kind of Golbaengi had different flavors and textures, it was fun! Golbaengi from the east sea is moist and chewy, while Golbaengi from the west sea is tenderer and has a sweet flavor!

I loved them both, but I personally liked Golbaengi from the west sea better because it was meatier! 🥺🧡 Golbaengi tang had a deep, spicy flavor! It really hits the spot and goes great with Golbaengi Jjim. If you like seafood, I highly recommend trying these two dishes! 👍🏻 Thank you so much for watching today! Happy holidays everyone!❤️

If you love seafood ramen or seafood soup (Haemultang), I highly recommend trying Jukkumi shrimp ramen! ✨ Thank you for watching!🔥 I hope you are always healthy and happy! ❣

Hi, guys! Today I brought Budae Bokkeum (Stir-fried sausage)! 🍚 I added ramen noodles and a slice of cheese and brought radish kimchi and rice topped with a sunny-side-up egg! I later added some spicy peppers so it got extra spicy! I tried Budae Bokkeum for the first time the other day, and it was so delicious! It was even better than expected. I wanted to make it with ramen noodles and peppers and introduce this food to you guys because this is also kind of new to me! 🙃 There are various kinds of ham, sausages, crown daisies, sesame leaves, and cabbage in it! The ingredients are basically the same as Budae Jjigae, so the taste is very familiar but slightly different! I think it’s a great mix of stir-fried sausages and Budae Jjigae the key is adding ramen and topping it with cheese! I ate it with ham and sausages, and it was so good!!! It’s delicious to eat it with rice with a sunny-side-up egg or wrap it with Gim (Dried-seaweed) ! I personally thought it would be tastier to make it extra spicy, so I added peppers, and it was a great decision! Since it’s sweet, salty, and sour, I bet anyone would love this! If you love Budae Jjigae or stir-fried sausage, you’ll definitely love it! If you haven’t ate it yet, I highly recommend trying it! Thank you so much for watching!

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はご飯が進むプデポックムを用意しました🍚ラーメンの替え玉にチーズも一枚追加しました！それに大根キムチと目玉焼きもご飯の上にのせました！ 途中で切っておいた辛い唐辛子もたっぷり入れて辛さを追加して食べました！ 先日プデポックムをプレゼントしてもらい、家で初めて食べてみたのですが、期待以上においしかったです！ 今回はラーメンの替え玉と唐辛子も入れてしっかり食べたかったし、それなりに馴染みのないメニューなので紹介したかったです！ 🙃 様々なハムやソーセージ、春菊、エゴマの葉、キャベツも入っていて、プデチゲと材料がほぼ同じです！ 馴染みがありながらも違う味！ ケチャップを入れたソーセージ野菜炒めとプデチゲが混ざった味に近いかな！ チーズがとろとろしたラーメンの替え玉が絶品ですが、ソーセージ&ハムと一緒に添えて食べると天国の味！黄身を割った白米にプデポックムをのせて食べてもとてもおいしいです。また、海苔と包んで食べても本当に豊かな味！ 個人的には辛ければもっとおいしそうと思って、辛い唐辛子を切って入れたんですが、やはり素晴らしい選択でした👏甘酸っぱい+甘しょっぱいので、誰もが好きになると思います！ プデチゲやソーセージ野菜炒めが好きな方に最高のメニュー！ まだ召し上がっていないなら、ぜひ一度召し上がってみることをおすすめします! 今日も視聴してくださる方々に 本当にありがとうございます！

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membawa Budae Bokkeum (sosis goreng)! 🍚 Saya menambahkan mie ramen dan sepotong keju dan membawa kimchi lobak dan nasi dengan telur goreng! Saya kemudian menambahkan beberapa paprika pedas sehingga menjadi lebih pedas! Saya mencoba Budae Bokkeum untuk pertama kalinya beberapa hari yang lalu, dan rasanya sangat enak! Itu bahkan lebih baik dari yang diharapkan. Saya ingin memperkenalkan makanan ini kepada kalian karena ini juga baru bagi saya! 🙃 Ada berbagai macam ham, sosis, mahkota aster, daun wijen, dan kol di dalamnya! Bahan-bahannya pada dasarnya sama dengan Budae Jjigae, jadi rasanya sangat familiar tapi sedikit berbeda! Saya pikir ini adalah campuran sosis goreng dan Budae Jjigae yang luar biasa! Kuncinya adalah menambahkan ramen dan menambahkan keju! Saya memakannya dengan ham dan sosis, dan itu sangat enak!!! Enak dimakan dengan nasi dengan telur goreng atau dibungkus dengan Gim (Rumput laut kering)! Saya pribadi berpikir akan lebih enak untuk membuatnya lebih pedas, jadi saya menambahkan paprika, dan itu adalah keputusan yang bagus! Karena manis, asin, dan asam, saya yakin siapa pun akan menyukai ini! Jika Anda menyukai Budae Jjigae atau sosis goreng, Anda pasti akan menyukainya! Jika Anda belum mencobanya, saya sangat merekomendasikan untuk memakannya! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton!

Hi, guys! 🙇🏻‍♀ Today I brought 1kg of eels! I roasted them super crispy and ate them with spicy green onion kimchi I made the other day! I also LOVE eels so much, and I was craving eels so much, so I bought good-quality eels! 💸🤤 My wallet got thin, but it really was worth it! I roasted it on a pan and then air-fried it, so it got golden brown and super crispy! I was able to enjoy chewy and moist textures at the same time! 😭 It just melted away in my mouth! It wasn’t fishy or anything, so I just kept eating and eating nonstop! I think roasted eel goes great with ginger, of course, but I think the best combo is roasted eel and spicy green onion kimchi!! ⸝⸝ʚ̴̶̷̆ ̯ʚ̴̶̷̆⸝⸝ I could eat it every single day, LITERALLY. Eels are really tasty and good for your health!🙊 I highly recommend trying roasted eel with green onion kimchi! 👍🏻Thank you so much for watching today! Hope you are always healthy and happy! ❣

Hi, guys! On the day we make green onion kimchi, we need to have this! That's Black bean noodles (Chapaghetti)!!!!! The best combination ever, which is black bean noodles & green onion kimchi! I prepared sunny-side-up egg, cheese sauce, and spicy chili pepper powder 🤤 I bought fresh green onion at the market and made green onion kimchi with it! Green onion kimchi is the most delicious on the day after it's made 🙏🏻 I knew how tasty it is to eat spicy and sweet green onion kimchi with black bean noodles, but it was always so touching! I added cheese to make black bean noodles stickier, and also added spicy chili pepper powder to make it spicier so that I could enjoy Chapaghetti in three ways! 🙌 I ate almost as I did the dishes due to the tasty black bean noodles and green onion kimchi 🙃 This combination is worth trying! I hope you could also make green onion kimchi at home by following my recipe and enjoying it with black bean noodles! Then, you could feel real happiness 🙊 Thank you for watching my video today!

Kemudian, Anda bisa merasakan kebahagiaan sejati 🙊 Terima kasih telah menonton video saya hari ini!

Herkese selam! Bugün evde kimchi yapmak için basit Gimjang (Kimchi Yapımı) yaptım! Bugün büyük ve taze istiridye getirdim ve istiridye Bossam yedim! Kimchi sayesinde çok mutlu oldum! Hi, guys! 🙇🏻‍♀ I made Spicy Mandu Jeongol (Dumpling Hot Pot) today! It's a very famous mandu in Korea, and the Korean comedian Yeong-Ja Lee highly recommended it (Called Kokkiri Mandu)! I made spicy kimchi jeongol with kimchi mandu! I also brought steamed kimchi mandu, white kimchi, and spicy radish kimchi! It's getting cold here in Korea, which means… it's the time of the year to eat jeongol! This mandu is so famous and delicious that it takes 2 months to get to buy it! I was also really curious, and then I finally got a chance to buy it! When I first tried it, I was actually surprised because it tasted so familiar! It reminded me of my mom's homemade kimchi mandu! 😳 It didn't taste artificial at all! It was like the epitome of kimchi mandu! Both the mandu skin and stuffing were very moist, I loved it! Since it was pretty spicy, the mandu jeongol was so delicious! Eating it alone is delicious as well, of course. 🤤 It was so good and went great with both radish kimchi and white kimchi! I basically inhaled it 😂 I highly recommend trying this kimchi mandu if you get a chance! How about eating spicy mandu jeongol today? 😉 Thank you so much for watching! Hope you are always healthy and happy! ❣

Halo semuanya!  Saya membuat Mandu Jeongol Pedas (Panci Pangsit) hari ini! Ini adalah mandu yang sangat terkenal di Korea, dan komedian Korea Yeong-Ja Lee sangat merekomendasikannya (Disebut Kokkiri Mandu)! Saya membuat kimchi jeongol pedas dengan kimchi mandu! Saya juga membawa kimchi mandu kukus, kimchi putih, dan kimchi lobak pedas! Di Korea semakin dingin, yang berarti… ini waktunya makan jeongol! Mandu ini begitu terkenal dan lezat sehingga butuh 2 bulan untuk membelinya! Saya juga sangat penasaran, dan akhirnya saya mendapat kesempatan untuk membelinya! Saat pertama kali mencobanya, saya justru kaget karena rasanya yang familiar! Itu mengingatkan saya pada kimchi mandu buatan ibu saya! Sama sekali tidak terasa buatan! Itu seperti lambang kimchi mandu! Baik kulit mandu dan isiannya sangat lembab, saya menyukainya! Karena rasanya cukup pedas, mandu jeongolnya sangat enak! Makan sendirian juga enak, tentu saja. Itu sangat enak dan cocok dengan kimchi lobak dan kimchi putih! Aku menghirupnya 😂! Saya sangat merekomendasikan mencoba kimchi mandu ini jika Anda mendapat kesempatan! Bagaimana kalau makan mandu jeongol pedas hari ini? Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! Semoga Anda selalu sehat dan bahagia!

Hi, guys! Today, I prepared grilled Daechang(Beef's large intestine), which was crispy on the outside and moist on the inside!! 💦🎉 I grilled fresh and thick Daechang until it became crispy! 🙊 I had it with seasoned chives, kimchi, pickled onion, fire chicken sauce, and sweet soy sauce! And I prepared a highball for drink 🙏🏻 I was so surprised because the large intestine was thicker than I expected! It was my first time trying grilled whole intestine, and its texture was amazing! It was crispy on the outside but super moist on the inside! While eating, I got some grease in the intestine on my face 🙃 Even though grilled crispy intestine was so savory and tasty, it was too greasy ... So you should prepare spicy seasoned chives and kimchi when you eat grilled large intestine! It might not be good for health, but anyway I happened to have lots of vegetables due to it... So it can be said to be good(?) for health, though! Next time, I will grill the large intestine much more crispier and enjoy it with spicy side dishes 😋 Thank you for watching my video today!

Hai kawan! Hari ini, saya menyiapkan Daechang (usus besar daging sapi) panggang, yang renyah di luar dan lembab di dalam!! Saya memanggang usus sapi segar dan tebal sampai menjadi renyah! Saya memilikinya dengan sayuran berbumbu, kimchi, acar bawang, saus ayam pedas nuklir, dan kecap manis! Dan saya menyiapkan highball untuk diminum 🙏🏻 Saya sangat terkejut karena usus besar lebih tebal dari yang saya harapkan! Ini adalah pertama kalinya saya mencoba panggang seluruh usus, dan teksturnya luar biasa! Itu renyah di luar tapi super lembab di dalam! Saat makan, saya mendapat minyak di wajah saya! Meskipun usus besar daging sapi panggang yang renyah begitu gurih dan lezat, itu terlalu berminyak ... Jadi Anda harus menyiapkan sayuran berbumbu pedas dan kimchi saat Anda makan usus besar bakar! Hi, guys 🙇🏻‍♀ It's quite chilly here in Korea these days! On chilly days like this, I tend to have cravings for hot anchovy noodles (Janchi-Guksu)! I also bought mini kimbap at the market, and easily made anchovy noodles at home! For side dishes, I prepared homemade spicy fresh kimchi and spicy sauce for noodles! Since the anchovy-based broth had such a deep flavor, I guzzled down the noodles so much! A bunch of toppings, which I added into the noodles, made the dish much tastier! There is nothing tastier than the noodles in themselves, even without the spicy sauce, but the sauce made the noodles much more perfect 🙊 Ah! You know that we must prepare kimbap when eating noodles, right? By having a bite of noodles, kimbap, and kimchi at the same time, I became happier 🥺A bowl of hot noodles helped me to keep myself warm and relaxed! Hot anchovy noodle is so tasty but really easy to make! How about simply making and enjoying tasty anchovy noodles at home? Thank you for watching my video today! Please always be happy and healthy❣

Hi, guys! Today I brought Buldak Glass Noodles & 3 kinds of Corn dogs with a cheese dip! I’m such a huge mala lover, so when I saw Mala Buldak Glass Noodles at the convenience store, I couldn’t resist it! I wasn’t sure what side dishes I should eat today at first, but I chose corn dogs! It was a great decision because it goes great with corn dogs! The combo of spiciness, thick sauce, sweetness, and crispiness was just AMAZING! I think Mala Buldak Glass Noodles are the spiciest glass noodle cup ramen on the market! It’s got a pretty strong mala flavor, so I strongly recommend trying it if you love malatang! The corn dogs were cream cheese, Spicy Ramen, and double cheese potato flavor, and they were all so delicious! I especially liked Spicy Ramen corn dog because it’s got a strong spicy flavor and is also super crispy! Corn dogs are well-known for going well with Tteokbokki together, but they also go really well with glass noodles! It tasted even better with a cheese dip! It was such a satisfying meal! 😘 I strongly recommend trying corn dogs when eating Mala Buldak Glass Noodles! Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Ini memiliki rasa mala yang cukup kuat, jadi saya sangat menyarankan untuk mencobanya jika Anda menyukai malatang! Hot dog Korea terkenal cocok dengan Tteokbokki bersama, tetapi mereka juga sangat cocok dengan mie transparan! Rasanya lebih enak dengan saus keju! Itu adalah makanan yang sangat memuaskan! Hi, guys! Today I brought the must-eat food during fall, gizzard shad!!! I bought fresh gizzard shads at the fish market near my place and prepared gizzard shad sashimi & grilled gizzard shad! 👏 I brought 3 kinds of sashimi today: whole gizzard shad sashimi, sekkosi (thin-cut sashimi), and thick-cut sashimi! In Korea, gizzard shads are one of the most popular foods during fall! Since I picked big ones, they had such a rich flavor! People say you should eat the fishbones as well, so I did! Even the bones were so soft! This was my first time trying whole gizzard shad sashimi, and I just fell in love with the texture! This has become another of my favorite foods! The grilled gizzard shads were also delicious! Since it tastes so good and has been well-loved for such a long time, we even have a saying for this: even a daughter-in-law who left her family comes back home to eat gizzard shads! Since the gizzard shads themselves have a rich flavor, I just sprinkled some salt and air-fried it, and it had such a deep flavor! Gizzard shads are now in season in Korea! I strongly recommend trying gizzard shads this fall before the winter comes around! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membawa makanan yang harus dimakan saat musim gugur, ikan ampela shad!!! Saya membeli ikan segar di pasar ikan dekat tempat saya dan menyiapkan sashimi & ikan bakar! Saya membawa 3 jenis sashimi dalam berbagai bentuk hari ini: ikan utuh, sekkosi (sashimi potongan tipis), dan sashimi potongan tebal! Di Korea, ikan ini (gizzard shads) adalah salah satu makanan paling populer selama musim gugur! Karena saya memilih yang besar, rasanya sangat kaya! Orang bilang kamu harus makan tulang ikan juga, jadi aku makan! Bahkan tulangnya sangat lembut! Ini adalah pertama kalinya saya makan sashimi ikan utuh, dan saya langsung jatuh cinta dengan teksturnya! Ini telah menjadi salah satu makanan favorit saya! Ikan bakarnya juga enak! Karena ikan ampela shad sendiri memiliki rasa yang kaya, saya hanya menaburkan sedikit garam dan menggorengnya, dan rasanya sangat dalam! Ikan gizzard shad sekarang sedang musim di Korea! Saya sangat merekomendasikan mencobanya musim gugur ini sebelum musim dingin tiba! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton hari ini! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Giant Braised Beef Ribs (Galbijjim)! I also brought spicy Geotjeori (fresh Kimchi) and rice! I bought big-sized beef ribs and cooked it with Vietnamese peppers, Korean Cheongyang peppers, and red peppers! The first taste was sweet and salty but it had a spicy finish! Since I brought it to a boil for a long time, the meat was super moist and tender! The meat separated from the bone automatically!

It was by far the best galbi I've ever tried! It was cooked perfectly and tasted just right! It was the best adrenaline rush! 😘 I also added chestnuts and carrots, and they were so sweet and tasty! I also ate spicy Kimchi (Geotjeori) with beef ribs and it tasted amazing! I was able to enjoy today's dish the whole time because it had a nice spicy finish! It's really easy to cook as long as you have enough time! I strongly recommend your own briased beef ribs (Galbijjim)  at home! Thank you so much for watching! I hope you are always healthy and happy ❣

Hi, guys! Today I made sundae jeongol! I used beef broth, the sundae in the fridge, mushrooms, onions, sesame leaves, cheongyang chilies, sauce, and udon noodles! I also steamed some sundae! The sauces for sundae were salt, chogochujang, and makjang! The sundae was traditional-style sundae, and it was my first time making sundae jeongol with it! The taste was somewhere between sundaeguk and gopchang jeongol! It was unbelievably delicious! 😭🧡 Since it was very savory but spicy (I added lots of spicy chili powder), it also went great with udon noodles! The sundae in the jeongol absorbed lots of broth, so it was so good!!! I ate steamed sundae with garlic, chilies, and lots of sauces, and it was also delicious! Today's dish was a perfect stress reliever! Sundae jeongol goes great with rice, of course, but it's also a great side dish for alcohol and hangover food! If you love sundae, I strongly recommend making sundae jeongol with lots of sundae! Thank you so much for watching! Hope you are always healthy and happy! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membuat sundae jeongol (hot pot sosis darah Korea)! Saya menggunakan kaldu sapi, sundae di lemari es, jamur, bawang, daun wijen, paprika pedas, saus, dan mie udon! Saya juga menyiapkan sundae kukus! Saus untuk sundae adalah garam, chogochujang, dan makjang! Sundae adalah sundae bergaya tradisional, dan ini adalah pertama kalinya saya membuat sundae jeongol dengannya! Rasanya ada di antara sundaeguk dan gopchang jeongol! Itu luar biasa lezat! Karena sangat gurih tapi pedas (saya menambahkan banyak bubuk cabai pedas), itu juga cocok dengan mie udon! Sundae di jeongol menyerap banyak kaldu, jadi enak banget!!! Saya makan sundae kukus dengan bawang putih, cabai, dan banyak saus, dan rasanya juga enak! Hidangan hari ini adalah penghilang stres yang sempurna! Sundae jeongol cocok dengan nasi, tentu saja, tetapi juga merupakan lauk yang enak untuk alkohol dan makanan mabuk! Jika Anda menyukai sundae, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat sundae jeongol dengan banyak sundae! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! Semoga Anda selalu sehat dan bahagia! 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はスンデ鍋を作りました！ 牛骨スープに水を入れて冷凍庫にあったスンデたっぷり、きのこ、玉ねぎ、ゴマの葉、激辛唐辛子、タレ、うどんまで入れれば終わり！ スンデも少し蒸しました👀スンデにつけて食べるソースには塩、酢コチュジャン、マクジャンを持ってきました！ 韓国伝統のスンデみたいな柔らかいスンデなんですけど、鍋にして食べるのは初めてでした！ 皆さんも初めてご覧になりますか？ 味はスンデスープとホルモン鍋の間の味というか？！ 一口食べたのですが信じられないほどおいしかったです😭🧡香ばしくて辛い方なので(辛い唐辛子粉をいっぱい入れたからかもしれません🙃)ぷりぷりしたうどん麺も一緒に食べてとても良かったです！ 鍋の中に入ったスンデはスープがたっぷり染み込んで美味しさアップグレード！蒸したスンデはニンニクと唐辛子を一緒に添えて、いろんなソースにつけて食べると本当においしかったです！ ほかほかのスンデ鍋をいっぱい食べて、しっかり癒された気分です！ (ご飯と食べるにもいいですが、酔い覚まし/おつまみにも超おすすめ)🥺スンデ好きな方はスンデたっぷり入れてスンデ鍋を一度作ってみてください! 今日も視聴してくださってありがとうございました！ いつも元気で幸せになってください！ 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! The other day I managed to buy the highest quality beef! (It was on a first-come, first-served basis!) So, to celebrate my success, I made beef sashimi Mulhoe! (Beef tartare with spicy cold soup) I also brought noodles, rice, kimchi, and Maekbanseok Gyeran (stone-plate cooked Eggs)! All I did was add sliced pears and cucumbers, lots of fresh, good-quality beef, and pour broth! It was super simple but surprisingly delicious! The beef sashimi had a very strong meaty flavor. Eating it alone was delicious, of course, but it was even tastier with other ingredients and broth! Since I’m a carb lover, I also added noodles and rice to the Mulhoe, and it tasted heavenly. I basically inhaled them! 😂If you have no appetite, you MUST try this!!! I’m dying to eat it again… 🥺 If you love beef sashimi or Mulhoe, I highly recommend trying beef Mulhoe! Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I made soy sauce marinated shrimps, using giant jumbo shrimp 🦐 I bought fresh jumbo shrimps in season and marinated them with spicy soy sauce! I also prepared soybean paste stew with crab & sunny-side-up eggs! Those jumbo shrimps were really giant, weren't they? They were as big as king tiger shrimps! It was my first time to marinate jumbo shrimps! I'm not sure, but they were much chewier than normal shrimps for me! They were sweet and savory enough to make me happy.. Since I added lots of spicy chili pepper into the soy sauce, and placed spicy chili pepper toppings onto those shrimp before I ate, the dish was spicy and salty as well as sweet! 😲 Even the sweet and savory soybean paste stew with zucchini and homemade tofu was perfect.. It's easier to make soy sauce marinated shrimp than you think! You can also make it at home, using jumbo shrimps which are in season now!!!!!!!! Thank you for watching my video today :)

Hi, guys! Today, I prepared 🔥 the best spicy food combination 🔥 of Spicy Curry Ramyun (Spicy Curry Teumsae Ramyun) & Spicy chili pepper kimchi! This combination was shortlisted in my favorite combinations.. Both of them are tasty in themselves, but they went perfectly well with each other..! It was my first time to try Spicy Curry Teumsae Ramyun, and it felt like eating spicy curry at a curry restaurant! Due to the potato toppings, I was willing to mix the curry sauce with rice.. but the sauce was not enough.. Ah! I think we need kimchi when eating curry.. Well-fermented spicy chili pepper kimchi was really spicy but refreshing.. 🙊 Savory sunny side-up eggs went also well with the noodles! Because it was even spicier than I had expected, it would be good for you to add cheese if you don't like spicy foods! If you like spicy curry, how about trying spicy curry Ramyun that I tried today! You need to prepare kimchi and sunny side-up eggs as well 🥺 Thank you so much for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Spicy Braised Shrimp and Fish Roe! Side dishes are steamed eggs, Gopchang Gim (Thick seaweed), and Geotjeori (Fresh Kimchi)! I made it with pollack roe in the fridge, plump shrimp, milt, and lots of bean sprouts! It was so delicious that I couldn’t believe I actually made it myself! 😂 The sauce was pleasantly salty, so it went great with wasabi soy sauce or Geotjeori! The harmony of savory pollack roe, milt, crunchy bean sprouts, and plump shrimp was just amazing!!! 🥲🧡 I also ate the cheese steamed eggs and Gopchang Gim-wrapped shrimp every once in a while. Hi, guys! Today I made aged kimchi jjigae with lots of spicy chili powder, pork, and ramen noodles! 👀 Side dishes are Gyeranmari (rolled omelet) and Gim (seaweed)! They’re a must when eating kimchi jjigae. I also brought rice with a fried egg! 💛 For kimchi jjigae, pork and kimchi are the two most important ingredients! Since I used fresh pork and well-aged kimchi, it was a huge success! The kimchi was aged for a long time, it had a deep and savory flavor! I cut the pork into thick pieces, but it was still so tender and juicy! The Gyeranmari also went great with the jjigae! I ate the mix of a fried egg, rice, and kimchi jjigae with Gim and it tasted AMAZING!!! 😭 No wonder kimchi jjigae is one of the most well-loved foods in Korea. If you love Korean food, I highly recommend making kimchi jjigae with well-aged kimchi and pork! Thank you for watching!

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membuat kimchi jjigae tua dengan banyak bubuk cabai pedas, babi, dan mie ramen! Lauk pauknya adalah Gyeranmari (telur dadar gulung) dan Gim (rumput laut)! Mereka adalah suatu keharusan saat makan kimchi jjigae. Saya juga membawa nasi dengan telur goreng! Untuk kimchi jjigae, daging babi dan kimchi adalah dua bahan terpenting! Karena saya menggunakan daging babi segar dan kimchi yang sudah tua, itu sukses besar! Kimchi sudah berumur lama, rasanya yang dalam dan gurih! Saya memotong daging babi menjadi potongan-potongan tebal, tetapi masih sangat empuk dan berair! Gyeranmari juga cocok dengan jjigae! Saya makan campuran telur goreng, nasi, dan kimchi jjigae dengan Gim dan rasanya LUAR BIASA!!! Tidak heran kimchi jjigae adalah salah satu makanan yang paling disukai di Korea. Jika Anda menyukai makanan Korea, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat kimchi jjigae dengan kimchi dan babi yang sudah tua! Terima kasih telah menonton!

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日は辛い唐辛子たっぷり、豚肉たくさんに、ラーメン玉まで入れて熟成キムチチゲを作りました！ 👀キムチチゲの必須おかず、卵焼きと海苔をご用意しました！ ご飯の上に目玉焼きまでのせました💛キムチチゲには豚肉とキムチが一番重要な材料です！ 新鮮な豚肉に長い間熟成させた熟成キムチの組み合わせなので、おいしくないわけがない！熟成キムチは長く熟成させ、深く香ばしい味が強かったです！ 豚肉は厚く切ったのに、とても柔らかくて肉汁がたっぷり！ ラーメンの替え玉にもチゲの汁が染み込んで本当においしかったです！ 柔らかい卵焼きもスープにつけてキムチをのせて食べると天国の味！目玉焼きご飯にキムチチゲを入れて混ぜて海苔で包んで食べると気絶！ 🤦🏻‍♀️ やっぱり韓国人のソウルフード、韓国料理の最高峰はキムチチゲだと改めて思いました。 韓国料理が好きな方は、熟成キムチと豚肉で熟成キムチチゲを作ってみてください！ 今日も視聴してくださって本当にありがとうございます:)

Spicy fire chicken Jjamppong had the rich taste of meat! I thought it would taste like fire chicken noodle soup, but it was much tastier than I expected! A lot of dried meat flakes are included, and it tastes like real meat Jjamppong! Juicy beef brisket made rich Jjamppong much more delicious 😭 Chewy and soft beef brisket.. It went well with thick noodles of fire chicken Jjamppong.. Soft and sticky sunny-side-up eggs also gave the noodles much deeper flavors... It was fantastic 😭 Since fire chicken Jjamppong had the meat flavors instead of seafood flavors, I'd like to recommend you to try it with beef brisket! If you like spicy foods, you would love it 🤭 Thank you for watching my video today :)

Hi, guys! Today I’m going to have Fume’s Homemakase (not omakase 😉)! I made this Japanese seafood rice bowl called Kaisendon with my favorite ingredients! 😋👏 Side dishes are sea trumpet (seaweed) , udon broth, scallions, pickled radish, pickled ginger, soy sauce for sashimi, and salt! I made it exclusively with my favorite seafood: sea urchin roe, sweet shrimp, scallop, and salmon roe! Honestly, you’ll love it as well as long as you love seafood 😂 I used tuna belly, Sunazuri, and swordfish belly! The rich, tender tuna, popping salmon roe, chewy sweet shrimp, tender scallop, and sweet sea urchin roe tasted just heavenly!  🥳 (I especially loved eating lots of soy sauce-marinated salmon roe at once)🥺! It felt like I was eating sushi because I put sashimi on the rice. I also ate sea trumpet-wrapped seafood, and it was so flavorful! 🥰 The ingredients are readily available online! I highly recommend enjoying Homemakase (omakase at Home) with your favorite seafood! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

(Saya paling suka makan telur salmon yang dimarinasi kecap sekaligus)🥺! Rasanya seperti saya sedang makan sushi karena saya menaruh sashimi di atas nasi. こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はおまかせじゃなくてプメの*ホームマカセ*!!!!! 私が好きな材料をあれこれ使って日本式海鮮丼！ 作りました😋👏（海鮮丼という和風シーフード丼です🐟）甘鯛とうどんのスープ、おかず（らっきょう、たくあん、酢生姜）、ソースは刺身醤油&塩を一緒に用意して食べました！ 私が好きな海産物であるウニ、マグロ、甘エビ、貝柱、イクラをたっぷり入れて作りました(正直言って、海産物が好きな方ならみんな好きだと思います! 😂）マグロの大トロ/砂ずり、そしてメカジキのトロを使用しました！ 貝柱は刺身用のホタテ貝柱です！ 🥳 油がさらさら溶ける香ばしいマグロにプチプチ弾ける塩味のイクラ、もっちりとした甘エビ、柔らかいホタテ貝柱、そして甘いウニまで本当においしくてビックリするほどでした(特に醤油に漬けたイクラをいっぱいすくって食べると幸せそのもの)🥺! 刺身をご飯の上に乗せて食べたらお寿司のような気もしました！ 海産物を柔らかい甘苔で包んで食べたら風味がすごかったです！ 材料はインターネットで簡単に手に入れることができるんですよ！ 海産物が好きな方は家でホームマカセで

Hi, guys! Today I made Cheese Pork Cutlet Rice Bowl (Katsudon)! It's super easy, I think basically anyone can make it! 🥳🧡 Side dishes are fried giant prawns, potato balls I made myself (I made it with potatoes, spam, and sweetcorn), pickled radish, and sour kimchi! I whipped it up with the ingredients (enoki mushrooms, frozen pork cutlet, chives, and eggs) I had in the fridge! The key is adding lots of onions. It's super easy to cook but incredibly delicious! 😳 The cheese in the pork cutlet was so chewy! Since it was cooked with the sauce, it was so soft and moist! It was even tastier to eat it with the fries! I'm glad I brought fries today 😂 They were so good! The sauce was sweet and salty, but it wasn't too salty, so it tasted just right! (I think it'd be a great side dish for drinks as well!) 😳 Both the texture and taste were amazing! It was tasty to eat it with fried eggs or Yeolmu kimchi! I also dipped it into the peanut sauce, and it was so delicious as well! If you love spicy enoki mushrooms, I highly recommend trying today's meal! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! today I prepared the most delicious combo in the world ⸝⸝ʚ̴̶̷̆ ̯ʚ̴̶̷̆⸝⸝: 2 bowls of Jjajangmyeon & Well-fermented Chili Kimchi & Crab Meat Fried Rice & Jjamppong broth & Spicy Chili Powder & Pickled Radish! 🤤 The chili kimchi I made is now fermented just right! Which means... it’s time to eat jjajangmyeon! In my defense, Chapaghetti and jjajangmyeon are two different foods! 😂 The 3 must-eat foods when making spicy chili kimchi are Chapaghetti, Jjajangmyeon, and Ramen! ❤️‍🔥 I was craving jjajangmyeon lately anyway, so it was perfect timing! The chili kimchi wrapped with jjajangmyeon was so good! For a second, it felt like I was born to eat this 😂 After eating some, I added spicy chili powder to the jjajangmyeon. It got spicy and so delicious! Pickled radish is, of course, a perfect side for jjajangmyeon as well! Since the sauce was so delicious, I just had to eat fried rice as well! I mixed the leftover sauce and crab meat fried rice, and it was just so good!!!!!! 😭❤️ Well-fermented chili kimchi has a lot more refreshing taste than freshly made chili kimchi! Don’t forget to eat jjajangmyeon when eating chili kimchi! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I prepared famous Taiwanese spicy beef noodles & two kinds of dim sum (Xiaolongbao / Har Gow)! I also prepared chopped spicy chili pepper! 😆❤ "Super Hot Pot Beef Flavor Instant Noodles" is a really famous item one must buy when visiting Taiwan! When I visited Taiwan with my mom, I purchased it a lot (I think I had original flavors instead of spicy ones 🤔) Anyway, we can easily get it here in Korea! It comes with large pieces of beef toppings, and you would really love it if you like beef noodles! Mala flavors are not that strong and it's as spicy as Shin Ramyun! I felt as if I was in Taiwan! Even dim sum made it much tastier! 😭🧡 Har gow dim sum is quite chewy and Xiaolongbao has lots of beef juice! The broth had so deep flavors of beef that I even cleared the broth! If you like Taiwanese beef noodles, you should try this! 👍 Always be healthy and happy 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini, saya menyiapkan mie daging sapi pedas Taiwan yang terkenal & dua jenis dim sum (Xiaolongbao / Har Gow)! Saya juga menyiapkan cabai pedas cincang! ❤ "Mie Instan Rasa Daging Sapi Super Hot Pot" adalah item yang sangat terkenal yang harus dibeli saat mengunjungi Taiwan! Ketika saya mengunjungi Taiwan dengan ibu saya, saya membelinya banyak (saya makan rasa asli pada waktu itu ) Bagaimanapun, kita dapat dengan mudah mendapatkannya di sini di Korea! Itu datang dengan potongan besar topping daging sapi, dan Anda akan sangat menyukainya jika Anda suka mie daging sapi! Rasa mala tidak begitu kuat dan pedasnya seperti Shin Ramyun! Saya merasa seperti berada di Taiwan! Bahkan lebih enak saat makan bersama dim sum! Har betapa dim sum cukup kenyal dan Xiaolongbao memiliki banyak jus daging sapi! Kaldunya memiliki rasa daging sapi yang begitu dalam sehingga saya bahkan membersihkan kaldunya! Jika Anda suka mie daging sapi Taiwan, Anda harus makan ini! 👍 Sehat dan bahagia selalu 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はとても有名な台湾のマラウー肉麺カップ麺に点心2種類！(シャオロンバオ/ハガウ)をご用意しました！ 辛い唐辛子も食べててかけました！ 😆❤滿漢大餐のマラウー肉麺カップラーメンは、台湾旅行のショッピングバケットリストとして有名です！ 前に母と台湾旅行に行って来ていっぱい買ってきたんですが、（その時は辛い味じゃなくて普通の味だけだったと思います） 🤔とにかく、もう韓国でも手に入れられます！ 中に大きめで柔らかい肉が入っているのが特徴なのですが、牛肉麺が好きな方は大好きにならざるを得ない蒸し肉の味です！ マーラー味は思ったより弱くてほとんど感じられなかったようですが、辛さは辛ラーメンくらい？ 辛さだったと思います！ 食べていると、まさに台湾にいる気分！ 点心と一緒に食べてもっとおいしかったです！ 😭🧡ハガウ点心は完全にぷりぷりしてて、シャオロンバオは肉汁が スープまで飲み干せます！肉の味たっぷりのマーラー牛肉麺！ 牛肉タンメン好きな方は是非一度召し上がってみてください！ 👍いつも元気でお幸せに いれますように🙏🏻

Chào các bạn! Hôm nay, mình sẽ ăn hai loại dim sum với mì ly mì bò mala nổi tiếng của Đài Loan! (Tiểu long bao / Há cảo)! Mình sẽ rắc thêm ớt cắt nhỏ lên trên khi ăn! 😆❤ Mì bò Mala đã quá nổi tiếng trong danh sách các thứ cần mua khi đi du lịch Đài Loan! Mình cũng đã mua rất nhiều trong khi đi du lịch Đài Loan với mẹ mình trước đây (mình nghĩ chỉ có hương vị thông thường, không cay kiểu vị Mala 🤔) Dù sao, bây giờ các bạn có thể mua ở Hàn Quốc và dễ dàng thưởng thức! Đặc điểm nổi bật của mì này là có miếng thịt to và mềm, những ai thích mì bò sẽ rất thích hương vị của thịt bò này! Vị mala không quá nồng như mình nghĩ nên gần như mình không cảm nhận được. Có vị cay cay của ớt thôi! Khi ăn, bạn sẽ có cảm giác như đang ở Đài Loan! Mình đã ăn mì với dim sum và rất ngon! 😭🧡 Món dim sum há cảo hoàn hảo và tiểu long bao nhiều thịt ngon ngọt bên trong! Mình uống hết nước mì luôn vì quá ngon! Bạn nào thích mì bò thì nhất định phải thử nhé! 👍 Chúc các bạn luôn luôn khỏe mạnh và hạnh phúc 🙏🏻

مرحباً جميعاً! اليوم ، قمت بتحضير نودلز لحم بقري تايواني شهير ونوعين من ديم سوم (Xiaolongbao / Har Gow)! أنا أيضا أعددت الفلفل الحار المفروم! 😆❤ "نودلز فورية بنكهة اللحم البقري سوبر هوت بوت" هي عنصر مشهور حقًا يجب على المرء شراؤه عند زيارة تايوان! عندما زرت تايوان مع أمي ، اشتريتها كثيرًا (أكلت النكهات الأصلية في ذلك الوقت 🤔) على أي حال ، يمكننا الحصول عليها بسهولة هنا في كوريا! تأتي مع قطع كبيرة من طبقات اللحم البقري ، وستحبها حقًا إذا كنت تحب نودلز اللحم البقري! نكهات مالا ليست بهذه القوة وهي حارة مثل شين راميون! شعرت كما لو كنت في تايوان! حتى أنه كان ألذ عند تناول الطعام مع ديم سوم معًا! 😭🧡 هار كيف يكون ديم سوم مطاطيًا تمامًا وشياولونجباو لديه الكثير من عصير اللحم البقري! المرق كان يحتوي على نكهات عميقة جدًا من اللحم البقري لدرجة أنني قمت بتطهير المرق! إذا كنت تحب نودلز اللحم البقري التايواني ، فعليك أن تأكل هذا! 👍 كن دائمًا بصحة جيدة وسعيد

Hi, guys! Today I brought the ultimate combo, Cheese Potato Croquettes & Spicy Fire Chicken Noodles! The croquettes were super easy to make. It was really crispy, so it was kind of like hashbrowns, but the inside was like buttery and creamy mashed potato! (It kind of tasted like crispy Korean potato pancake as well!) Since I added sweetcorn and bacon, it was extra tasty! I think fire chicken noodles are definitely the best when eating something fried! It was way more delicious to eat fire chicken noodles and the croquettes together! The croquettes went great with the cheese sauce I brought and ketchup, but eating them alone tasted just right as well! I think it was because of the bacon I added. Since I sifted the mashed potato, it just melted in my mouth! I ate it when it was still hot, so the cheese was still very stretchy. It was so good!!! If you have potatoes at home, I highly recommend making Cheese Potato Croquettes! They would be a great snack for kids and a side dish for drinks! Thank you so much for watching today!

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membawakan kombo pamungkas, Kroket Kentang Keju & ​​Mie Ayam Api Pedas! Kroket sangat mudah dibuat. Itu benar-benar renyah, jadi itu seperti hashbrowns, tapi bagian dalamnya seperti kentang tumbuk mentega dan krim! (Rasanya seperti panekuk kentang Korea yang renyah juga!) Karena saya menambahkan jagung manis dan bacon, rasanya sangat enak! Saya pikir mie ayam api pasti yang terbaik saat makan sesuatu yang digoreng! Jauh lebih enak makan mie ayam api dan kroket bersama! Kroketnya sangat enak dengan saus keju yang saya bawa dan saus tomat, tetapi memakannya sendiri rasanya juga enak! Saya pikir itu karena bacon yang saya tambahkan. Karena saya menyaring kentang tumbuk, itu hanya meleleh di mulut saya! Saya memakannya saat masih panas, jadi kejunya masih sangat melar. Itu sangat bagus! Jika Anda memiliki kentang di rumah, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat Kroket Kentang Keju! Mereka akan menjadi camilan yang enak untuk anak-anak dan lauk untuk minuman! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton hari ini!

Hi, guys! Today, I made Gordon Ramsay's Beef Wellington!!!!! This is my first time to make Beef Wellington, but it was totally successful!!!!!!!! It was delicious beyond description.. 😭 How marvelous! Who said British cuisine might be unsavory..? I think the person who invented this is a genius! I purchased 2.1kg of beef tenderloin, removed the fascia and fat, and cut it into pieces! The beef was really chewy, juicy, and soft! The pastries on the outer part were crispy and buttery! The great harmony of them was great! Due to the salt on pastries made it salty as well as sweet and savory! Duxelles seche (button mushroom, garlic, shallot, and roasted chestnut) and bacon made the taste of beef much richer! Each ingredient had its own flavors even after they were cooked! Rather, they were in harmony! Grilled vegetables and sauces went well with the main dish! It was worth the effort! I hope you could also try to make this menu! Thank you for watching my video today!🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Chadolbagi (beef brisket) Jjamppong Sundubu (Spicy beef & seafood soft tofu)! ❤‍🔥 I added lots of soft tofu, seafood, and beef brisket and made it spicy and rich! Side dishes are fried eggs, white kimchi, pickled radish, and white rice! The seafood I added is cuttlefish, mussels, shrimp, and clams (for broth). I also brought various kinds of vegetables and stir-fried them in chili oil! I added chodubu (similar to soft tofu) and regular sundubu (soft tofu), poured in water, and seasoned it to taste. 😆🎶 The tofu just melted in my mouth. So mellow and savory. The broth was really rich because of the beef and seafood! 👍🏻 The beef brisket and the seafood were also delicious. So plump and well-seasoned. I ended up eating another bowl of rice 😂 I think today’s dish would be great hangover food or a side dish when drinking! Gangneung is famous for Jjamppong Sundubu! The Jjamppong Sundubu I ate is also Gangeung-style. If you love Sundubu, I highly recommend making it with lots of soft tofu, seafood, and meat! You’ll be surprised! Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

Hari ini saya membuat Chadol (sandung sapi) Jjamppong Sundubu (Spicy beef & seafood soft tofu)! ❤‍🔥 Saya menambahkan banyak tahu lembut, makanan laut, dan Sandung lamur sapi dan membuatnya pedas dan kaya! Lauk pauknya adalah telur goreng, kimchi putih, acar lobak, dan nasi putih! Makanan laut yang saya tambahkan adalah sotong, kerang, udang, dan kerang (untuk kaldu). Saya juga membawa berbagai macam sayuran dan menggorengnya dengan minyak cabai! Saya menambahkan chodubu (mirip tahu lunak) dan sundubu biasa (tahu lunak), dituangkan ke dalam air dan dibumbui secukupnya. Tahu baru saja meleleh di mulutku. Begitu lembut dan gurih. Kaldunya sangat kaya karena daging sapi dan makanan lautnya! 👍🏻 Sandung lamur dan makanan lautnya juga enak. Begitu montok dan dibumbui dengan baik. Saya akhirnya makan semangkuk nasi lagi 😂 Saya pikir hidangan hari ini akan menjadi makanan mabuk yang enak atau lauk saat minum! Gangneung terkenal dengan Jjamppong Sundubu! Jjamppong Sundubu yang saya makan juga bergaya Gangeung. Jika Anda menyukai Sundubu, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuatnya dengan banyak tahu lembut, makanan laut, dan daging! Anda akan terkejut! Terima kasih banyak untuk menonton hari ini! 🙏🏻

Today, I made Green Onion Kimchi Stew with thick and juicy pork belly 👏 I also prepared Rolled Omelet with Cheese, Stir-fried Shredded Potatoes, Seasoned Sesame Leaves, and a bowl of rice 😆 Ordinary cabbage kimchi stew is one of the most common foods Korean enjoy, but green onion kimchi stew is somewhat unfamiliar! Many Korean people might not have tried it yet! Green onion kimchi was well fermented, so I used it to make green onion kimchi stew 🤭 When I had a bite of pork belly with green onion kimchi, I was deeply surprised and thought "Wow, this is the best kimchi stew in my life"! Both pork belly and green onion kimchi were so soft! Green onion kimchi made juicy pork belly even more refreshing! And the broth was really deep and tasty 😭 There are things that are truly inseparable in the world! I think Kimchi stew and rolled omelet are one of them! Rolled omelet with cheese went well with green onion kimchi, and even better with kimchi stew broth! Stir-fried shredded potatoes that I made while making kimchi stew were so savory and tasty that they went perfectly well with kimchi stew as well! Also, it was good that I prepared seasoned sesame leaves, too! I think this is an incredible food combination👍🏻 I hope you can also make green onion kimchi stew with pork belly!!!!!! I'd like to strongly recommend it to you ✨ Thank you for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日は肉汁が弾ける厚いサムギョプサルをたっぷり入れてネギキムチチゲを作りました。 👏チーズ卵焼き、じゃがいも炒め、ゴマの葉の和え物、白ご飯を一緒に添えました😆白菜キムチを入れて煮込んだキムチチゲは韓国人によく食べるメニューですが、ネギキムチで煮込んだネギキムチチゲは、多少不慣れかもしれないです! 韓国人でも思ったより食べたことがない方が多いんです！ 冷蔵庫にネギキムチがとても食べやすいように熟してネギキムチチゲを食べるのにぴったりだと思ったんです🤭ネギキムチをサムギョプサルの上にのせて一口食べたら、最初の口を食べたらすぐに"わぁ、これは私の人生最高のキムチチゲだ"と思いました! サムギョプサルとネギキムチ、両方ともとても柔らかかったです！ サムギョプサルを噛むと肉汁がたっぷりこぼれますが、さっぱりとしたネギキムチの味で仕上げが完璧でした! スープも本当に蒸しておいしかったです😭世の中には落ちてはいけない宿命のような存在がいるでしょう？ 私はキムチチゲと卵焼きがそんな存在だと思います！ チーズ卵焼きにネギキムチをのせて食べてもとてもおいしいし、キムチチゲスープにつけて食べても最高! チゲを作りながら作ったジャガイモ炒めもさっぱり香ばしくてキムチチゲと一緒に添えて食べるのにとてもいいです! 香ばしいエゴマの葉の和え物もナイスチョイス! この組み合わせは本当に賞を受けなければならない組み合わせだと思います👍🏻ネギキムチを利用してサムギョプサルをいっぱい入れたネギキムチチゲを是非作って召し上がってみてください!!!!!!!超おすすめ✨今日も視聴していただき本当にありがとうございます! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Cheese Buldak Curry! Side dishes are Fried Prawns & 2 kinds of Homemade Kimchi. I added lots of Buldak sauce to Mom’s curry and then topped it with cheese, and it was so delicious! I had no idea curry and cheese would go so well together! It was sweet and savory but had a nice finish, and since the cheese stretched, it was just perfect! The fried prawns were so crispy and the kimchi (sour kimchi & geotjeori) was crunchy! Kimchi is definitely a must when eating curry! Since the curry was pretty spicy, it wasn’t greasy at all. And I used various kinds of ingredients and cut them into big pieces, so it was really flavorful! I wasn’t a fan of curry as a kid, but I think it’s because I didn’t know curry could taste like this back then! 😂 I cooked a friend this curry and she said this is the best curry she’s ever tasted! If you love curry, I highly recommend making Buldak curry topped with lots of cheese! Thank you so much for watching!🙏🏻
