Itu manis dan gurih tetapi memiliki hasil akhir yang bagus, dan karena kejunya melar, itu sempurna! Udang gorengnya sangat renyah dan kimchi (kimchi asam & Geotjeori) renyah! Kimchi jelas merupakan suatu keharusan saat makan kari! Karena karinya cukup pedas, rasanya tidak berminyak sama sekali. Dan saya menggunakan berbagai macam bahan dan memotongnya menjadi potongan-potongan besar, jadi itu benar-benar beraroma! Saya bukan penggemar kari saat kecil, tapi saya pikir itu karena saya tidak tahu kari bisa terasa seperti ini saat itu! Saya memasak kari ini dan memberikannya kepada teman saya! Dia bilang ini kari terbaik yang pernah dia rasakan 😂! Jika Anda menyukai kari, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat kari Buldak dengan banyak keju! Terima kasih banyak sudah menonton!🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はチーズプルダックカレーを作りました！ サクサク大正海老の天ぷらと家のキムチは2種類(酸っぱいキムチ/浅漬け)を一緒に添えました！ ママ印のカレーにプルダックソースたっぷり入れて(ママ目をつぶって下さい,,,),モッツァレラチーズもいっぱいかけて食べたら、美味!!!!!!! カレーとチーズがこんなによく似合う組み合わせだったんですか？ カレーの再発見！
甘くて香ばしい！仕上げは辛いのに、ぐんぐん伸びるこりこりしたチーズまで添えられてて、完璧そのもの！大正海老の天ぷらは揚げたてでカリカリ！酸っぱいキムチと浅漬けもカリカリ！ それこそ天上のハーモニー！ 🎶ほぼキムチ半分、カレー半分の比率で食べた気がします。やっぱりカレーはキムチと一緒に食べるともっとおいしいと思います！ 最後まで食べるのにカレーが辛くてさっぱり脂っこくもなかったです。具も多様で大きくて風味がすごかったです! 幼い頃はカレーがあまり好きではなかったようだが、その時このカレーを食べていたら！ カレーがとてもおいしくて、友達にあげたら本人が食べてみたカレーの中で一番おいしいと言いました😂とにかく!カレーが好きな方はプルダックソースをお好みで追加してチーズをのせて食べてみてください! 今日も視聴してくださって本当にありがとうございます！ 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! You should pay attention to today's video if you like spicy Chinese food!!!! Today, I prepared Sichuan-style spicy pork hot pot (Mala Jeongol) ❤️‍🔥 If you like hot and spicy flavors, you should try this menu!!!!! This is one of the spicy Sichuan-style dishes, and it comes with pork and various kinds of vegetables (bean sprouts, mushroom, pak choi, dried red pepper, and Chinese pepper, etc.)! I also prepared two kinds of Chinese dumplings (chives & egg / meat & celery), a bowl of rice, and pickled radish! I think it has the strongest flavor of spices among Mala dishes! It was so spicy that my lips got irritated a bit, but I really liked that 😍 Since it was quite salty, it went well with rice and dumplings! If you like spicy Chinese food, I hope you can try this when you have a chance!! Thank you for watching my video today :)

Hi, guys! Today is Chobok in Korea! 🔥Since It’s the hottest day of the year, we eat healthy foods. I made samgyetang with abalones & nurungi! I added ginseng, dates, ginkgo nuts, and green onions and stuffed the chicken with sticky rice and mung beans! I brought it to a boil for a long time. Side dishes are Deodeok muchim (seasoned deodeok) and 3 different kinds of kimchi: Chili kimchi, Green onion kimchi, and Altari kimchi! 😋 As you can tell from the color of the broth, it was so rich and delicious! 🥺 It was steaming hot, but samgyetang is most delicious when eating it out of a boiling pot!

In Korea, there are 3 days called Sambok. They indicate the beginning, middle, and end of the hottest days during summer. On these days, we eat hot, healthy foods so we can stay healthy and energized!

I ate the chicken with salt and green onion kimchi! Even the abalones were so chewy and delicious! I also ate them with Altari kimchi, cabbage kimchi, and deodeok muchim! It was so delicious and gave me lots of energy! 😂 We eat samgyetang during summer because it warms up our bodies and helps us become resistant enough to fight the heat! I do eat samgyetang regardless of the weather, though. I'm sure you guys have seen me eating samgyetang pretty often in my previous videos 😂. Anyway, it’s a lot easier to make than you think! I highly recommend eating samgyetang this summer! Thank you so much for watching 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini Chobok di Korea! Karena ini hari terpanas dalam setahun, kami makan makanan sehat. Saya membuat samgyetang dengan abalon & nurungi! Saya menambahkan ginseng, kurma, kacang ginkgo, dan daun bawang dan mengisi ayam dengan ketan dan kacang hijau! Saya merebusnya untuk waktu yang lama. Lauk pauknya adalah Deodeok muchim (deodeok berbumbu) dan 3 jenis kimchi yang berbeda: kimchi cabai, kimchi bawang hijau, dan kimchi Altari! Seperti yang Anda tahu dari warna kaldu, itu sangat kaya dan lezat! Panasnya mengepul, tapi samgyetang paling enak saat memakannya dari panci yang mendidih!

Di Korea, ada 3 hari yang disebut Sambok. Mereka menunjukkan awal, tengah, dan akhir dari hari-hari terpanas selama musim panas. Jadi, kita makan makanan panas dan sehat agar tetap sehat dan berenergi!

Saya makan ayam dengan garam dan kimchi bawang hijau! Bahkan abalonnya sangat kenyal dan lezat! Saya juga memakannya dengan Altari kimchi, kimchi kubis, dan deodeok muchim! Itu sangat lezat dan memberi saya banyak energi! 😂 Kami makan samgyetang selama musim panas karena menghangatkan tubuh kami dan membantu kami menjadi cukup tahan untuk melawan panas! Bagi saya, saya makan samgyetang terlepas dari cuaca. Saya yakin kalian sudah sering melihat saya makan samgyetang di video saya sebelumnya 😂. Bagaimanapun, ini jauh lebih mudah dibuat daripada yang Anda pikirkan! Saya sangat merekomendasikan makan samgyetang musim panas ini! Terima kasih banyak sudah menonton 🙏🏻

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日は韓国の"初伏"です。 🔥(一年の中で一番暑い日、健康を回復するためにスタミナ食を食べる日です)今日私はアワビとおこげ入りサムゲタンを作ってみました 😋高麗人参、ナツメ、銀杏、ネギを入れて鶏の中にはもち米と緑豆も入れて牛骨スープを入れて煮込みました! おかずはキムチ3種セット!!!! 唐辛子キムチ、ネギキムチ、アルタリキムチにツルニンジンの和え物も用意しました! スープの色を見れば分かると思いますが、スープが本当に濃くてとてもおいしかったです！🤦🏻‍♀️とても熱かったのですが、サムゲタンはあつあつの土鍋に温かく食べるのがまた魅力です! 昔から三伏(三伏:韓国では伝統的に一年の中で最も期間の始まり、中間、終わりを表す初伏、重複、末伏の3つの日があります)には⭐以熱治熱⭐つまり熱い食べ物で熱い夏を乗り越える風習があります！♨鶏肉の塩にたっぷりつけて食べて、ネギキムチものせて食べて、もちもち&まろやかなアワビもすごくおいしかった！ それにキムチ3種類とツルニンジンの和え物を交互に食べると、高騰する力があふれまくります！😂サムゲタンを夏の保養食として食べる理由は、お腹が温かくなり、元気が出て暑さに勝てる抵抗力が生まれるからだそうです！ 実は私は季節に関係なくサムゲタンを好んで食べる方ですが...(ブイログを見るとよく登場します🙃思ったより作りやすい韓国の代表スタミナ食「サムゲタン」！サムゲタンも食べて健康も一緒に食べてください! 今日も視聴してくださって本当にありがとうございます！ 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I prepared Yakisoba (Japanese stir-fried noodles)! I got as a gift "UFO Yakisoba", which is a famous Japanese Yakisoba cup noodle, so I made it with mayonnaise, Katsuobushi, and sunny-side-up eggs!!! I also prepared super long sausage, green onion kimchi, cheese sauce, and chopped spicy chili pepper 😋❤️‍🔥 It was so tasty that I couldn't believe it was just a cup of noodle ★ I had tried it once before, but it was much more delicious today! I think it's because of the various kinds of side dishes that I prepared today! It felt like real Japanese Yakisoba dishes due to sunny-side-up eggs, mayonnaise, and katsuobushi! The sauce was sweet and salty enough, and the noodles were really soft! Savory Kewpie mayonnaise and soft katsuobushi made a great harmony in my mouth! And sunny-side-up eggs, green onion kimchi, sausage... they were like avengers assemble!⭐️ And the plump sausages were really juicy! Green onion kimchi made it much more refreshing 🥳 Now I see why this Yakisoba cup noodle is so famous! I feel like getting this more and more as a gift 👀 If you like Yakisoba, how about this Yakisoba cup noodle with various kinds of toppings and side dishes? Thank you for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I prepared soy sauce marinated shrimp / spicy sauce marinated shrimp made with giant tiger shrimp 🦐 which is the most delicious, plump, and chewy marinated shrimp! I also prepared a bowl of rice, flying fish roe rice balls, yolk, and dried seaweed! As a final step, I made rice topped with marinated shrimp by putting chopped shrimp on rice and spreading sesame oil! 😋 (+ I used fresh king tiger shrimp, which can be made into marinated shrimp!) Original marinated shrimp (normal-sized shrimp) is also tasty, but marinated giant tiger shrimp that I tried for the first time in my life was really, really amazing!!!! I was worried whether the giant shrimp would not be well seasoned with the sauce, but it was a great mistake! I marinated the shrimp for three days, and it was totally well seasoned with the sauce! It tasted like chewy and plump marinated crab or lobster tail! It was like eating 10 pieces of original shrimp at once... The shrimp was not squishy at all but just really plump.. Soy sauce marinated shrimp was tasty, but spicy sauce marinated one was perfectly tasty as well! 👏 (Please give it a big hand) It went well with rice, and even more perfectly with flying fish roe rice balls, savory yolk, and dried seaweed! A bowl of rice topped with shrimp and sesame oil I had as a final step was really great! It was worth waiting for three days! If you like marinated shrimp, how about making the one with giant tiger shrimp!!!!!!!🤭 Thank you for watching my video today :)

Halo semuanya! Hari ini, saya menyiapkan udang marinasi kecap / udang marinasi saus pedas yang dibuat dengan udang windu raksasa! mana udang marinasi paling enak, montok, dan kenyal! Saya juga menyiapkan semangkuk nasi, bola nasi telur ikan terbang, kuning telur, dan rumput laut kering! Sebagai langkah terakhir, saya membuat nasi dengan udang yang diasinkan dengan meletakkan udang cincang di atas nasi dan mengolesi minyak wijen! (+ Saya menggunakan udang windu segar, yang bisa dibuat menjadi udang yang diasinkan!) Ukuran normal dari udang yang diasinkan juga enak, tetapi udang windu yang saya coba pertama kali dalam hidup saya benar-benar luar biasa! !!! Saya khawatir apakah udang raksasa tidak akan dibumbui dengan baik dengan saus, tetapi itu adalah kesalahan besar! Saya mengasinkan udang selama tiga hari, dan itu benar-benar dibumbui dengan saus! Rasanya seperti kepiting yang diasinkan atau ekor lobster yang kenyal dan montok! Rasanya seperti makan 10 potong udang biasa sekaligus... Udangnya tidak squishy sama sekali tapi benar-benar montok.. Udang yang dimarinasi kecap memang enak, tapi yang dimarinasi saus pedas juga sangat enak! Ini cocok dengan nasi, dan bahkan lebih sempurna dengan bola nasi telur ikan terbang, kuning telur yang gurih, dan rumput laut kering! Semangkuk nasi dengan udang dan minyak wijen yang saya miliki sebagai langkah terakhir benar-benar enak! Itu sepadan dengan menunggu selama tiga hari! Kalau kalian suka udang marinasi, gimana kalau bikin yang pake udang windu raksasa!!!!!!!🤭 Terima kasih sudah menonton video saya hari ini :)

Hi, guys! Today I ate Spicy Fire Naengmyeon (Songju Bulnaengmyeon 🔥) & Pork galbi! Songju Bulnaengmyeon is a Korean brand well-known for its spicy Naengmyeon! Their Naengmyeon (cold noodles) is the spiciest in Korea! I made Naengmyeon with the sauce from Songju Bulnaengmyeon and topped it with homemade radish Kimchi! I also boiled eggs! 🤤🧡 Naengmyeon is always delicious, but I think it's definitely the most delicious during summer! I mixed the sauce with the noodles and ate them with pork Galbi, radish Kimchi, and soft-boiled eggs. It was so refreshing and worked up my appetite! 😍 The radish Kimchi was super crunchy, and the galbi was so thick! Since I cut the meat into big pieces, it was extra tasty! You can never go wrong with Naengmyeon & pork Galbi! It's THE BEST! I highly recommend eating naengmyeon & pork galbi, it'll make you happy right away! 👏 Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya makan Spicy Fire Naengmyeon (Songju Bulnaengmyeon ) & Pork galbi! Songju Bulnaengmyeon adalah merek Korea yang terkenal dengan naengmyeon pedasnya! Naengmyeon mereka adalah yang terpedas di Korea! Saya membuat Naengmyeon (mie dingin) dengan saus dari Songju Bulnaengmyeon dan atasnya dengan lobak Kimchi buatan sendiri! Saya juga merebus telur! Naengmyeon (mie dingin) selalu enak, tapi menurutku ini pasti yang paling enak selama musim panas! Saya mencampur saus dengan mie dan memakannya dengan daging babi Galbi (babi yang diasinkan), lobak Kimchi, dan telur rebus. Itu sangat menyegarkan dan meningkatkan nafsu makan saya! 😍 Kimchi lobaknya super renyah, dan Galbinya sangat kental! Karena saya memotong daging menjadi potongan-potongan besar, itu sangat lezat! Anda tidak akan pernah salah dengan Naengmyeon & babi Galbi! Itu yang terbaik! Saya sangat merekomendasikan makan Naengmyeon & babi Galbi, itu akan membuat Anda bahagia segera! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I made Basil Cream Pasta with glass noodles! I used basil leaves I grew myself, 3 different kinds of glass noodles, and rolled rice paper! Side dishes are crispy hash brown, shrimp balls, and brown bread! I've been really into basil cream tteokbokki lately, so I thought it'd be really delicious to make spicy basil cream pasta with lots of glass noodles! I also added bacon, Vienna sausages, shrimp, and cheongyang chilies, so it was spicy and creamy! So delicious. Since the glass noodles were covered in thick basil sauce, the minute I tried it, it felt like my stress was gone! 👍🏻 It also had a subtle basil taste, so if you love basil like me, you'll definitely love today's food! 👀 The hash brown and shrimp balls dipped into the sauce were so tasty as well! The brown bread went great with the sauce! Both the texture and taste were perfect! If you love basil cream, I highly recommend making Basil Cream Pasta with Glass Noodles + Rice Paper + the ingredients you like! 🙏🏻 Thank you so much for watching!

Hi, guys! Today I made Spicy Rose Galbijjim (Braised beef short ribs)! I made it with 1kg of beef, lots of glass noodles, potatoes, and sweet pumpkin! I also brought tuna mayo rice balls, cheese Gyeranjjim (steamed eggs), and sour Kimchi! 😋🧡 If you're a fan of the rose sauce, I highly recommend trying this! ★ It's spicy but has a subtle tomato flavor, and the creamy rose sauce goes perfectly with the glass noodles and beef! Once you try it, you'll be addicted to it! 💦 The meat was well cooked, so it was easy to separate the meat from the bones! So tender and moist. And it was also slightly chewy at the same time! I loved it! The harmony of Galbijjim, tuna mayo rice balls, and cheese Gyeranjjim was indescribable! It was totally worth the time and effort! I think it would also be great to cook this for your friends when having a home party! 👏 If you love rose sauce, I highly recommend making rose Galbijjim! Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today’s food is spicy Mala Xiang Guo cup noodles! I brought 3 cups of Mala Xiang Guo(Chinese dried hot pot) Ramen topped with fried eggs and plump sausages, Creamy Shrimp, and Kkwobarou (Sweet and sour pork)! It was so good!!! 😭 ❤️ I loved that the mala flavor is pretty strong! The noodles are pretty wide but soft and chewy, and it comes with lots of veggie and dried tofu flakes! The fried eggs and sausages went great with it! Kkwobarou is a must when eating malatang or mala shang guo! I ate the Kkwobarou (Sweet and sour pork)-wrapped noodles and creamy shrimp every once in a while, it tasted heavenly 👏! If you crave a mala flavor, this will be perfect! If you like Mala Xiang Guo, I highly recommend trying it with extra ingredients you like! It’s so much tastier that way! Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Makanan hari ini adalah mie cangkir Mala Xiang Guo (hot pot kering Cina) pedas! Saya membawa 3 cangkir Mala Xiang Guo Ramen atasnya dengan telur goreng dan sosis montok, Udang Krim, dan Kkwobarou (Babi asam manis)! Itu sangat bagus! ❤️ Saya suka rasa malanya cukup kuat! Mienya cukup lebar tetapi lembut dan kenyal, dan dilengkapi dengan banyak sayuran dan serpihan tahu kering! Telur dan sosis goreng sangat cocok dengan itu! Kkwobarou adalah lauk wajib saat makan malatang atau mala shang guo! Saya makan Kkwobarou dan udang krim bersama-sama, rasanya surgawi ! Jika Anda menginginkan rasa mala, ini akan menjadi sempurna! Jika Anda menyukai Mala Xiang Guo, saya sangat merekomendasikan memakannya setelah menambahkan bahan tambahan yang Anda suka! Jauh lebih enak seperti itu! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I had scallops! 🔥 I prepared spicy braised scallops, which is really easy to make, with noodles, cheese sauce, sunny-side-up eggs, and a bowl of rice! I prepared it for those who like scallops 🙌 I ordered giant Korean scallops, and steamed them with spicy sauce!!!! Large scallops were so juicy! 💦🤭 Sweet juice of scallops went well with spicy sauce! It was a good thing that I prepared cheese sauce, too! I made it, by mixing mozzarella cheese & Emmental cheese sauce, and it went amazingly well with scallops! Having noodles seasoned with sesame oil and spicy sauce made me so happy.. It was my first time having scallops with sunny-side-up eggs, but it was really good 😢🧡 Scallops are always tasty!!! We can enjoy them in various ways, using different side dishes & sauces! If you like scallops, how about ordering them and making spicy braised scallops at home? I strongly recommend it 👏 Thank you for watching my video today 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today I brought the Japanese fried tofu udon! 🍢 I'm sure some of you guys already know this udon! (It's Nissin Donbei Kitsune Udon)! It's famous for coming with huge fried tofu. I think it's pretty popular with Koreans as well! I also brought a fish cake skewer (Eomuk), fried tofu pouches, crown daisies, and Korean chilies called cheongyang chilies so I could enjoy today's dish better! 😘 The side dishes are pizza pork cutlet, green onion kimchi, and pickled radish! The fried tofu was so sweet and soft! As I bit into it, the broth came out! I loved the katsuobushi taste 🥺 The noodles were plump but soft. Since I added various kinds of ingredients, it was even more delicious! I love the spiciness of the chilies! Also, I enjoyed the fish cake skewers and the fried tofu pouches with lots of seafood! As an udon lover, I really loved the deep-flavored broth! It totally hit the spot. If you have this fried tofu udon, I highly recommend making your own version of udon with your favorite ingredients! It'll be so much more delicious! Thank you so much for watching :)

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membawa udon tahu goreng Jepang! Saya yakin sebagian dari kalian sudah mengetahui udon yang satu ini! (Ini Nissin Donbei Kitsune Udon)! Ini terkenal karena datang dengan tahu goreng besar. Saya pikir itu cukup populer dengan orang Korea juga! Saya juga membawa tusuk sate ikan, kantong tahu goreng, sayuran, dan paprika pedas sehingga saya bisa menikmati hidangan hari ini dengan lebih baik! Saya juga membawa potongan daging babi pizza, kimchi bawang hijau, dan acar lobak! Tahu gorengnya sangat manis dan lembut! Saat saya menggigitnya, kaldunya keluar! Saya menyukai rasa katsuobushi ! Mienya montok tapi lembut. Karena saya menambahkan berbagai macam bahan, rasanya jadi lebih enak! Terutama, saya suka pedasnya cabai! Saya juga menikmati tusuk sate kue ikan dan kantong tahu goreng dengan banyak makanan laut! Sebagai pecinta udon, saya sangat menyukai kaldu rasa yang dalam! Itu membuatku sangat santai. Jika Anda memiliki tahu udon goreng ini, saya sangat merekomendasikan untuk membuat udon versi Anda sendiri dengan bahan-bahan favorit Anda! Ini akan menjadi jauh lebih lezat! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton :)

こんにちは、皆さん！ 今日はこの前もらった日本のきつねうどんを用意しました🍢すでにご存知の方はみんな知っている有名な日本のきつねうどんカップラーメン!!!(「日清どん兵衛きつねうどん」といいます)大きな油揚げが入っているのが特徴ですが、韓国内でもすごく有名です。 私は別におでん串と油揚げ袋、春菊、青陽唐辛子をのせて、私好みにもっとおいしく作ってみました😘ピザとんかつとネギキムチ、たくあんも一緒にご用意しました！ 大きな油揚げはすごく甘くて、とても柔らかくてびっくりしました🥺深いかつおぶしぶだし汁をたっぷり含んでいて本当においしかったです！ 一口食べるとスープが飛び出します！ 麺は厚みがありますが柔らかい食感！確かにいろいろな具材を追加して食べたのでもっとおいしく食べられたと思います！ みじん切り唐辛子を入れて深くて辛い味が芸術でした！ おでん串も美味しかったし、海鮮たっぷりの油揚げ袋もぴったり！ うどんが大好きなんですが、深いスープの味に癒されました！ 家にいなりうどんをお持ちの方はお好みに合わせて具材を追加してお召し上がりください！ 100倍おいしいです🙃! 今日も視聴してくださって本当にありがとうございます:)

Hi, guys! Today I brought a Japanese-style Huge Cheese Beef Stew! I used 3 kg of beef and made 10 servings of Beef Stew! I boiled it for about 4 hours, and bring it to a boil for a long time again with sauce. I also ate raw egg rice, sour kimchi, pickled radish, and various kinds of veggies! The sauce itself made me feel like eating a steak! It was really meaty and rich! The stew is really rich and since it was covered in the sauce, it was so delicious! Since the meat was tender and soft, and the sauce was rich, it tasted heavenly! I think it was even more delicious because I put mozzarella cheese at the end. Plus, the raw egg rice with sesame oil was THE BEST! I ate it with the stew, and it was mindblowing! If you love stew, I highly recommend making beef stew with big pieces of beef! It’s rich and so delicious. It’ll put a smile on your face! Thank you so much for watching!

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membawa Cheese Beef Stew besar ala Jepang! Saya menggunakan 3 kg daging sapi dan membuat 10 porsi Rebusan Daging Sapi! Saya merebusnya selama sekitar 4 jam, dan didihkan lagi untuk waktu yang lama dengan saus. Saya juga makan nasi telur mentah, kimchi asam, acar lobak, dan berbagai jenis sayuran! Sausnya sendiri membuat saya merasa ingin makan steak! Itu benar-benar gemuk dan kaya! Karena dagingnya empuk dan lembut, dan sausnya kaya, rasanya surgawi! Menurut saya lebih enak lagi karena saya taruh keju mozzarella di bagian akhir. Plus, telur mentah di atas nasi dengan minyak wijen adalah yang terbaik! Saya memakannya dengan rebusan, dan itu luar biasa! Jika Anda menyukai rebusan, saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat sup daging sapi dengan potongan besar daging sapi! Ini kaya dan sangat lezat. Itu akan membuat Anda tersenyum! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton!

Hi, guys! Today I made spicy Altang (Spicy Fish Roe Soup) with lots of fish roe! 🔥(Altang & Aljjim (Braised Spicy Fish Roe) that are made with pollack roe are very popular dishes in Korea) I also brought Altari Kimchi (Young Radish Kimchi), a Cheese Hamburg Steak, Fried Eggs, and White Rice! 😋 I first made Altang with lots of fresh pollack roe (I also often roast it with butter, it's so good), and since the roe was fresh, it was pretty big but super soft! It was surprisingly delicious! 💦 The soup was pretty spicy, so it went great with the roe! I ate nonstop 😂 The combo of Altari kimchi and fried eggs was also amazing! I also ate the homemade tofu in the Altang with the rice and it was so good! Eating the hamburg steak once in a while was also great, it was just perfect! (I made Hamburg steaks myself and kept them in the fridge) Making Altang is super easy to cook but also delicious and healthy! I highly recommend making Altang with lots of pollack roe! Thank you so much for watching! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya membuat Altang (Sup Telur Ikan Pedas) pedas dengan banyak telur ikan! (Altang & Aljjim (Roe Ikan Pedas Rebus) yang dibuat dengan telur pollack adalah hidangan yang sangat populer di Korea) Saya juga membawa Altari Kimchi (Kimchi Lobak Muda), Steak Hamburg Keju, Telur Goreng, dan Nasi Putih! Saya pertama kali membuat Altang dengan banyak pollack roe segar (saya juga sering memanggangnya dengan mentega, itu sangat enak), dan karena roenya segar, itu cukup besar dan sangat lembut! Itu sangat lezat! Supnya cukup pedas, jadi cocok dengan telurnya! Saya makan tanpa henti 😂 Kombo Altari kimchi dan telur goreng juga luar biasa! Saya juga makan tahu buatan sendiri di Altang dengan nasi dan itu enak! Makan steak hamburg sesekali juga enak, itu sempurna! (Saya membuat steak Hamburg sendiri dan menyimpannya di lemari es) Membuat Altang pedas sangat mudah dimasak tetapi juga lezat dan sehat! Saya sangat merekomendasikan membuat Altang pedas dengan banyak pollack roe! Terima kasih banyak telah menonton! 🙏🏻

Hi, guys! Today, I made Japanese style Tomato Hayashi Rice (Hai Rice) 🍅! I also prepared rice, soft scrambled eggs, and homemade spicy green onion kimchi! I've heard tomato Hayashi rice is really delicious, so I've been wondering what it tastes like! I almost fainted the moment I had the first bite!!!! It tasted like sour, sweet, and delicious tomato soup, but the deeper flavor was brought out! Anyway, it was really delicious, and had familiar but interesting flavors! When I boiled the sauce, I could smell the scent of tomato, and it was much tastier than I expected!!!!! The scrambled egg was so soft that it melted like snow in my mouth! Since the buttery egg was savory, it went well with sour and sweet tomato Hayashi sauce! Spicy, sweet, and crunchy green onion kimchi made the dish much tastier! Anyone, who likes hai rice sauce or not, would like this combination 😭 It's because the Hayashi rice is amazingly delicious! If you have a chance, you need to try this! It will be a taste that you will never forget!! Thank you for watching my video today! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini, saya membuat Tomat Hayashi Rice (Hai Rice) ala Jepang ! Saya juga menyiapkan nasi, telur orak-arik lembut, dan kimchi bawang hijau pedas buatan sendiri! Saya pernah mendengar nasi tomat Hayashi benar-benar enak, jadi saya bertanya-tanya seperti apa rasanya! Saya hampir pingsan saat gigitan pertama!!!! Rasanya seperti sup tomat asam, manis, dan lezat, tetapi rasa yang lebih dalam dibawa keluar! Bagaimanapun, itu sangat lezat, dan memiliki rasa yang akrab tetapi menarik! Ketika saya memasak, saya bisa mencium aroma tomat, dan itu jauh lebih enak dari yang saya harapkan!!!!! Orak-arik telurnya begitu lembut hingga meleleh seperti salju di mulutku! Karena telur rasa mentega itu gurih, itu cocok dengan saus tomat Hayashi yang asam dan manis! Kimchi bawang hijau yang pedas, manis, dan renyah membuat rasanya lebih enak! Ada yang suka hai rice sauce atau tidak, pasti suka kombinasi ini ! Itu karena nasi Hayashi sangat enak! Jika Anda memiliki kesempatan, Anda harus mencoba ini! Ini akan menjadi rasa yang tidak akan pernah Anda lupakan!! Terima kasih telah menonton video saya hari ini! 🙏🏻

Chào các bạn! Hôm nay mình làm món cơm sốt cà chua Hayashi kiểu Nhật Bản 🍅! Mình ăn cùng với trứng sữa chiên mềm, kim chi hành lá và cơm trắng! Sốt cà chua Hayashi! Mình nghe nói rất ngon nên mình thực sự rất tò mò sẽ có mùi vị như thế nào! Ngay khi ăn miếng đầu tiên, vị ngon đến nỗi mình suýt ngất!!!! Hi, guys! Today I'm going to harvest the Ssamchu (Korean lettuce) I grew myself! So I brought Ssamchu, lettuce, water parsely in season, Jeyukbokkem, Ureong Gangdoenjang (Soybean paste stew with freshwater snails), green onion Kimchi, and Gyeranmari! I made a wrap with the Jeyukbokkem, lettuce, Ssamchu, water parsley, Ureong Gangdoenjang, and green onion Kimchi and it was so delicious that I was this close to crying 😂 Since I grew them myself, it tasted even more delicious! The Ureong(freshwater snails) was so chewy and tasty that eating it with rice alone was good enough! Of course, it tastes even better with Jeyukbokkem! I also recommend trying green onion kimchi and Jeyukbokkem or Gyeranmari, Jeyukbokkem, and green onion Kimchi! I'm sure once you try this combo, you'll be addicted to it! And I also highly recommend harvesting ssamchu yourself! It's really delicious. Thank you so much for watching today! 🙏🏻

Halo semuanya! Hari ini saya memanen Ssamchu yang saya tanam sendiri! Jadi saya membawa Ssamchu, selada, air parsely di musim, Jeyukbokkem, Ureong Gangdoenjang (rebusan pasta kedelai dengan siput air tawar), daun bawang Kimchi, dan Gyeranmari! Saya membuat bungkus dengan Jeyukbokkem, selada, Ssamchu, peterseli air, Ureong Gangdoenjang, dan Kimchi bawang hijau! Sangat lezat sampai saya hampir menangis 😂 Karena saya menanamnya sendiri, rasanya lebih enak! Ureong (siput air tawar) sangat kenyal dan enak sehingga memakannya dengan nasi saja sudah cukup enak! Tentu saja, rasanya lebih enak dengan Jeyukbokkem! Saya juga merekomendasikan untuk mencoba kimchi bawang hijau dan Jeyukbokkem atau Gyeranmari, Jeyukbokkem, dan Kimchi bawang hijau! Saya yakin sekali Anda mencoba kombinasi ini, Anda akan ketagihan! Dan saya juga sangat merekomendasikan memanen ssamchu sendiri! Ini benar-benar lezat. Terima kasih banyak untuk menonton hari ini! 🙏🏻

Đó là combo quá hợp quá ngon!!!! ★ Rau sống tự tay mình trồng thêm các loại rau khác nữa, thịt heo xào xay, canh tương đậu lên men nấu ốc, kim chi hành lá và trứng cuộn ★ Mình đã chuẩn bị tất cả! Thực sự ngon đến mức mình suýt rơi nước mắt… Bởi vì là rau mình tự trồng nên có vẻ ngon hơn nữa! Canh tương đậu nấu với ốc, ốc có vị dai giòn thấm đều nước canh tương đậu, món này cũng rất ấn tượng! Sự kết hợp này là kiểu bữa ăn tại nhà theo phong cách Hàn Quốc, ăn một lần là muốn ăn tiếp nữa đấy! Ah!!!! Rau sống thực sự rất ngon, các bạn hãy thử trồng nhé 😎 (?) Herkese selam! Bugün kendim yetiştirdiğim Ssamchu'yu hasat ettim! Bu yüzden mevsiminde Ssamchu, marul, su parseli, Jeyukbokkem, Ureong Gangdoenjang (tatlı su salyangozlu soya ezmesi güveç), yeşil soğan Kimchi ve Gyeranmari'yi getirdim! Jeyukbokkem, marul, Ssamchu, su maydanozu, Ureong Gangdoenjang ve yeşil soğan Kimchi ile sarma yaptım! O kadar lezzetliydi ki ağlamaya bu kadar yakındım 😂 Kendim yetiştirdiğim için tadı daha da lezzetli oldu! Ureong (tatlı su salyangozları) o kadar çiğnendi ve lezzetliydi ki, onu yalnızca pirinçle yemek bile yeterince iyiydi! Tabii ki Jeyukbokkem ile daha da lezzetli! Ayrıca yeşil soğan kimchi ve Jeyukbokkem veya Gyeranmari, Jeyukbokkem ve yeşil soğan Kimchi'yi denemenizi tavsiye ederim! Bu kombinasyonu denediğinizde eminim bağımlısı olacaksınız! Ayrıca ssamchu'yu kendiniz hasat etmenizi şiddetle tavsiye ederim! Gerçekten çok lezzetli. Bugün izlediğiniz için çok teşekkürler! 🙏🏻
